                    214
                    3x
                    
                      
         attr(body, "query") <- qp[1]

                    		
                  

                  

                    215
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    216
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    217
                    3x
                    
                      
      return(body)

                    		
                  

                  

                    218
                    
                    
                      
    }) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    219
                    
                    
                      
    # Flatten the list of responses (one list of data per batch) into one single list

                    		
                  

                  

                    220
                    3x
                    
                      
    purrr::list_flatten()

                    		
                  

                  

                    221
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    222
                    3x
                    
                      
  if (length(body_list) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    223
                    2x
                    
                      
    cli::cli_warn("No results found for the given query in {.val {endpoint}}.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    224
                    2x
                    
                      
    if (tidy) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    225
                    1x
                    
                      
      return(tibble::tibble())

                    		
                  

                  

                    226
                    
                    
                      
    } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    227
                    1x
                    
                      
      return(list())

                    		
                  

                  

                    228
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    229
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    230
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    231
                    
                    
                      
  # --- 8. Output Formatting ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    232
                    
                    
                      
  # Return as-is if tidy=FALSE (cleaned list structure)

                    		
                  

                  

                    233
                    1x
                    
                      
  if (!tidy) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    234
                    
                    
                      
    # Basic cleanup: replace NULLs with NA in list elements

                    		
                  

                  

                    235
                    !
                    
                      
    res <- body_list %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    236
                    !
                    
                      
      purrr::map(function(x) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    237
                    !
                    
                      
        if (is.list(x) && length(x) > 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    238
                    !
                    
                      
          x[purrr::map_lgl(x, is.null)] <- NA

                    		
                  

                  

                    239
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    240
                    !
                    
                      
        return(x)

                    		
                  

                  

                    241
                    
                    
                      
      })

                    		
                  

                  

                    242
                    !
                    
                      
    return(res)

                    		
                  

                  

                    243
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    244
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    245
                    
                    
                      
  # --- 9. Tidy Conversion ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    246
                    
                    
                      
  # Convert the parsed JSON (list of lists) into a tidy tibble.

                    		
                  

                  

                    247
                    1x
                    
                      
  res <- body_list %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    248
                    1x
                    
                      
    purrr::map(function(x) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    249
                    2x
                    
                      
      q_attr <- attr(x, "query")

                    		
                  

                  

                    250
                    2x
                    
                      
      if (is.list(x) && length(x) > 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    251
                    
                    
                      
        # Replace NULLs with NA so they don't disappear during tibble conversion

                    		
                  

                  

                    252
                    2x
                    
                      
        x[purrr::map_lgl(x, is.null)] <- NA

                    		
                  

                  

                    253
                    2x
                    
                      
        row <- tibble::as_tibble(x)

                    		
                  

                  

                    254
                    !
                    
                      
        if (!is.null(q_attr)) row <- dplyr::bind_cols(query = q_attr, row)

                    		
                  

                  

                    255
                    2x
                    
                      
        return(row)

                    		
                  

                  

                    256
                    !
                    
                      
      } else if (is.null(x) || length(x) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    257
                    !
                    
                      
        return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    258
                    
                    
                      
      } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    259
                    
                    
                      
        # Primitive values (strings/numbers) are wrapped into a 'value' column

                    		
                  

                  

                    260
                    !
                    
                      
        row <- tibble::tibble(value = x)

                    		
                  

                  

                    261
                    !
                    
                      
        if (!is.null(q_attr)) row <- dplyr::bind_cols(query = q_attr, row)

                    		
                  

                  

                    262
                    !
                    
                      
        return(row)

                    		
                  

                  

                    263
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    264
                    
                    
                      
    }) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    265
                    1x
                    
                      
    purrr::list_rbind()

                    		
                  

                  

                    266
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    267
                    1x
                    
                      
  return(res)

                    		
                  

                  

                    268
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    269
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    270
                    
                    
                      
#' Generic Cheminformatics API Request Function

                    		
                  

                  

                    271
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    272
                    
                    
                      
#' This specialized template handles the nested payload structure common to the

                    		
                  

                  

                    273
                    
                    
                      
#' EPA cheminformatics microservices: {"chemicals": [{"sid": "ID1"}], "options": {...}}

                    		
                  

                  

                    274
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    275
                    
                    
                      
#' @param query A character vector of identifiers (DTXSIDs, etc.)

                    		
                  

                  

                    276
                    
                    
                      
#' @param endpoint The specific sub-path (e.g., "toxprints/calculate")

                    		
                  

                  

                    277
                    
                    
                      
#' @param options A named list of parameters to be placed in the 'options' JSON field.

                    		
                  

                  

                    278
                    
                    
                      
#' @param sid_label The key used for identifiers in the JSON body (usually "sid").

                    		
                  

                  

                    279
                    
                    
                      
#' @param server Global environment variable name for the base URL (default: 'chemi_burl').

                    		
                  

                  

                    280
                    
                    
                      
#' @param auth Boolean; whether to include the API key header. Defaults to FALSE.

                    		
                  

                  

                    281
                    
                    
                      
#' @param pluck_res Optional character; the name of the field to extract from the JSON response.

                    		
                  

                  

                    282
                    
                    
                      
#' @param wrap Boolean; whether to wrap the query in a {"chemicals": [...], "options": ...} structure.

                    		
                  

                  

                    283
                    
                    
                      
#'        Defaults to TRUE. If FALSE, sends a JSON array of objects like [{"sid": "ID1"}, ...].

                    		
                  

                  

                    284
                    
                    
                      
#' @param tidy Boolean; whether to convert the result to a tidy tibble. Defaults to TRUE.

                    		
                  

                  

                    285
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ... Additional arguments passed to httr2.

                    		
                  

                  

                    286
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    287
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A tidy tibble (if tidy=TRUE) or a raw list.

                    		
                  

                  

                    288
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    289
                    
                    
                      
generic_chemi_request <- function(query, endpoint, options = list(), sid_label = "sid", 

                    		
                  

                  

                    290
                    
                    
                      
                                  server = "chemi_burl", auth = FALSE, pluck_res = NULL, 

                    		
                  

                  

                    291
                    
                    
                      
                                  wrap = TRUE, tidy = TRUE, ...) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    292
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    293
                    
                    
                      
  # 1. Base URL Resolution

                    		
                  

                  

                    294
                    3x
                    
                      
  base_url <- Sys.getenv(server, unset = server)

                    		
                  

                  

                    295
                    !
                    
                      
  if (base_url == "") base_url <- server

                    		
                  

                  

                    296
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    297
                    
                    
                      
  # 2. Input Normalization

                    		
                  

                  

                    298
                    3x
                    
                      
  query <- unique(as.vector(query))

                    		
                  

                  

                    299
                    3x
                    
                      
  query <- query[!is.na(query) & query != ""]

                    		
                  

                  

                    300
                    !
                    
                      
  if (length(query) == 0) cli::cli_abort("Query must be a character vector.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    301
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    302
                    
                    
                      
  # 3. Payload Construction

                    		
                  

                  

                    303
                    3x
                    
                      
  chemicals <- purrr::map(query, ~ set_names(list(.x), sid_label))

                    		
                  

                  

                    304
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    305
                    3x
                    
                      
  if (wrap) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    306
                    2x
                    
                      
    payload <- list(

                    		
                  

                  

                    307
                    2x
                    
                      
      chemicals = chemicals,

                    		
                  

                  

                    308
                    2x
                    
                      
      options = options

                    		
                  

                  

                    309
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    310
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    311
                    1x
                    
                      
    payload <- chemicals

                    		
                  

                  

                    312
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    313
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    314
                    
                    
                      
  # Check environment flags

                    		
                  

                  

                    315
                    3x
                    
                      
  run_debug <- as.logical(Sys.getenv("run_debug", "FALSE"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    316
                    3x
                    
                      
  run_verbose <- as.logical(Sys.getenv("run_verbose", "FALSE"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    317
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    318
                    3x
                    
                      
  if (run_verbose) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    319
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_rule(left = paste('Generic Chemi Request:', endpoint))

                    		
                  

                  

                    320
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_dl(c('Number of items' = '{length(query)}'))

                    		
                  

                  

                    321
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_rule()

                    		
                  

                  

                    322
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_end()

                    		
                  

                  

                    323
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    324
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    325
                    
                    
                      
  # 4. Request building

                    		
                  

                  

                    326
                    3x
                    
                      
  req <- httr2::request(base_url) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    327
                    3x
                    
                      
    httr2::req_url_path_append(endpoint) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    328
                    3x
                    
                      
    httr2::req_method("POST") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    329
                    3x
                    
                      
    httr2::req_body_json(payload) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    330
                    3x
                    
                      
    httr2::req_headers(Accept = "application/json")

                    		
                  

                  

                    331
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    332
                    3x
                    
                      
  if (auth) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    333
                    1x
                    
                      
    req <- req %>% httr2::req_headers(`x-api-key` = ct_api_key())

                    		
                  

                  

                    334
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    335
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    336
                    
                    
                      
  # 5. Debugging

                    		
                  

                  

                    337
                    3x
                    
                      
  if (run_debug) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    338
                    2x
                    
                      
    return(httr2::req_dry_run(req))

                    		
                  

                  

                    339
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    340
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    341
                    
                    
                      
  # 6. Execution

                    		
                  

                  

                    342
                    1x
                    
                      
  resp <- httr2::req_perform(req)

                    		
                  

                  

                    343
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    344
                    
                    
                      
  # 7. Response Processing

                    		
                  

                  

                    345
                    1x
                    
                      
  if (httr2::resp_status(resp) < 200 || httr2::resp_status(resp) >= 300) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    346
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_abort("Chemi API request to {.val {endpoint}} failed with status {httr2::resp_status(resp)}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    347
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    348
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    349
                    1x
                    
                      
  body <- httr2::resp_body_json(resp, simplifyVector = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    350
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    351
                    1x
                    
                      
  if (!is.null(pluck_res)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    352
                    !
                    
                      
    body <- purrr::pluck(body, pluck_res)

                    		
                  

                  

                    353
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    354
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    355
                    1x
                    
                      
  if (length(body) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    356
                    !
                    
                      
    if (tidy) return(tibble::tibble()) else return(list())

                    		
                  

                  

                    357
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    358
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    359
                    !
                    
                      
  if (!tidy) return(body)

                    		
                  

                  

                    360
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    361
                    
                    
                      
  # 8. Tidy Conversion

                    		
                  

                  

                    362
                    !
                    
                      
  if (!tidy) return(body)

                    		
                  

                  

                    363
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    364
                    
                    
                      
  # Handle cases where body is a named list of results (keyed by query)

                    		
                  

                  

                    365
                    1x
                    
                      
  if (!is.null(names(body)) && !is.data.frame(body)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    366
                    !
                    
                      
      res <- body %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    367
                    !
                    
                      
        purrr::map(function(x) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    368
                    !
                    
                      
          if (is.list(x) && length(x) > 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    369
                    !
                    
                      
            x[purrr::map_lgl(x, is.null)] <- NA

                    		
                  

                  

                    370
                    !
                    
                      
            return(tibble::as_tibble(x))

                    		
                  

                  

                    371
                    
                    
                      
          } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    372
                    !
                    
                      
            return(tibble::tibble(value = x))

                    		
                  

                  

                    373
                    
                    
                      
          }

                    		
                  

                  

                    374
                    
                    
                      
        }) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    375
                    !
                    
                      
        purrr::list_rbind(names_to = "query_id")

                    		
                  

                  

                    376
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    377
                    
                    
                      
      # If body is an unnamed list, we attempt to match it back to the query 

                    		
                  

                  

                    378
                    
                    
                      
      # if the counts match exactly, otherwise we just bind.

                    		
                  

                  

                    379
                    1x
                    
                      
      res <- body %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    380
                    1x
                    
                      
        purrr::map(function(x) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    381
                    2x
                    
                      
          if (is.list(x) && length(x) > 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    382
                    
                    
                      
            # Check for name collisions or nested lists

                    		
                  

                  

                    383
                    2x
                    
                      
            x[purrr::map_lgl(x, is.null)] <- NA

                    		
                  

                  

                    384
                    
                    
                      
            # We use try as some deeply nested chemi-results might fail direct as_tibble

                    		
                  

                  

                    385
                    2x
                    
                      
            t_res <- try(tibble::as_tibble(x), silent = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    386
                    !
                    
                      
            if (inherits(t_res, "try-error")) return(tibble::tibble(data = list(x)))

                    		
                  

                  

                    387
                    2x
                    
                      
            return(t_res)

                    		
                  

                  

                    388
                    !
                    
                      
          } else if (is.null(x) || length(x) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    389
                    !
                    
                      
            return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    390
                    
                    
                      
          } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    391
                    !
                    
                      
            return(tibble::tibble(value = x))

                    		
                  

                  

                    392
                    
                    
                      
          }

                    		
                  

                  

                    393
                    
                    
                      
        }) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    394
                    1x
                    
                      
        purrr::list_rbind()

                    		
                  

                  

                    395
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    396
                    
                    
                      
      # If the results match the query length, add the query column

                    		
                  

                  

                    397
                    1x
                    
                      
      if (nrow(res) == length(query) && !"dtxsid" %in% colnames(res)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    398
                    !
                    
                      
         res <- dplyr::bind_cols(dtxsid = query, res)

                    		
                  

                  

                    399
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    400
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    401
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    402
                    1x
                    
                      
  return(res)

                    		
                  

                  

                    403
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' @title Use the ClassyFire API to classify a chemical structure

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#' @description This function takes a SMILES string as input, submits it to

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#'   ClassyFire, polls for the result, and returns the classification.

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' @param query A character vector of SMILES strings to classify.

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @returns A list containing the ClassyFire classification results.

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' \dontrun{

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' util_classyfire(query = "OC(=O)C1=C(C(O)=O)C(C(O)=O)=C(C(O)=O)C(C(O)=O)=C1C(O)=O")

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
util_classyfire <- function(query) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
  # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
  # --- Error handling

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
  # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
  # --- Check if query is missing

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    !
                    
                      
  if (missing(query)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_abort("The `query` argument is missing. Please provide a SMILES string.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
  # --- Check if query is a character vector

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    !
                    
                      
  if (!is.character(query)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_abort("The `query` argument must be a character vector of SMILES strings.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
  # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
  # --- Get environment variables

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
  # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    !
                    
                      
  ctx_burl <- Sys.getenv("np_burl", unset = NA)

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    !
                    
                      
  run_debug <- as.logical(Sys.getenv("run_debug", unset = "FALSE"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    !
                    
                      
  run_verbose <- as.logical(Sys.getenv("run_verbose", unset = "FALSE"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    !
                    
                      
  if (is.na(ctx_burl)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_abort("The `np_burl` environment variable is not set. Please set it to the base API URL.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
  # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
  # --- Debugging information

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
  # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    !
                    
                      
  cli::cli_rule(left = "ClassyFire payload options")

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    !
                    
                      
  cli::cli_dl(c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
    "Number of compounds" = "{length(query)}"

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
    # ,"Base URL (ctx_burl)" = "{ctx_burl}",

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
    # "Debug mode (run_debug)" = "{run_debug}",

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
    # "Verbose mode (run_verbose)" = "{run_verbose}"

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
  ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    !
                    
                      
  cli::cli_rule()

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    !
                    
                      
  cli::cli_end()

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    
                    
                      
  # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      
  # --- Create the request wrapper

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    
                    
                      
  # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    !
                    
                      
  safe_classify_and_get_result <- purrr::possibly(

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
    .f = function(current_query, current_index, total_queries) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    !
                    
                      
      if (run_verbose) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    !
                    
                      
        cli::cli_alert_info("({current_index}/{total_queries}) Submitting SMILES for classification: {current_query}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
      # --- Build submission request ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    !
                    
                      
      req_classify <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    !
                    
                      
        httr2::request(ctx_burl) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    !
                    
                      
        httr2::req_url_path_append(path = "/chem/classyfire/classify") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    !
                    
                      
        httr2::req_headers("accept" = "application/json") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    !
                    
                      
        httr2::req_url_query(smiles = current_query) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    !
                    
                      
        httr2::req_timeout(5) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    !
                    
                      
        httr2::req_retry(

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    !
                    
                      
          max_tries = 10,

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    !
                    
                      
          is_transient = ~ httr2::resp_is_transient(.x) || httr2::resp_status_class(.x) == "server"

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
        )

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      
      # --- Handle debug mode (dry run) ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    !
                    
                      
      if (run_debug) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    !
                    
                      
        cli::cli_alert_info("Dry run for submission request:")

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    !
                    
                      
        httr2::req_dry_run(req_classify)

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    !
                    
                      
        cli::cli_alert_info("Dry run for result request (using placeholder job_id '12345'):")

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    !
                    
                      
        req_result_dryrun <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    !
                    
                      
          httr2::request(ctx_burl) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    !
                    
                      
          httr2::req_url_path_append(path = "/chem/classyfire/12345/result") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    !
                    
                      
          httr2::req_headers("accept" = "application/json")

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    !
                    
                      
        httr2::req_dry_run(req_result_dryrun)

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    
                    
                      
      # --- Perform submission ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    !
                    
                      
      resp_classify <- httr2::req_perform(req_classify)

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    
                    
                      
      # --- Validate submission response ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    !
                    
                      
      submission_status <- httr2::resp_status(resp_classify)

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    !
                    
                      
      if (submission_status != 200) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    !
                    
                      
          cli::cli_alert_danger("Unexpected HTTP status {submission_status} during submission for SMILES: {current_query}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    !
                    
                      
          if (submission_status != 429) { # 429 is handled by httr2::req_retry

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    !
                    
                      
              return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    
                    
                      
          }

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    !
                    
                      
      job_id <- httr2::resp_body_json(resp_classify)$id

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    
                    
                      
      # ! Temporary: print job_id

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    !
                    
                      
      print(paste("Job ID:", job_id))

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    !
                    
                      
      if (is.null(job_id)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    !
                    
                      
        cli::cli_alert_danger("Could not find job ID in submission response for SMILES: {current_query}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    !
                    
                      
        return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    !
                    
                      
      if (run_verbose) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    !
                    
                      
        cli::cli_alert_success("({current_index}/{total_queries}) Submission successful. Job ID: {job_id}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    
                    
                      
        #cli::cli_alert_info("({current_index}/{total_queries}) Polling for results for job ID: {job_id}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    
                    
                      
      # --- Poll for results ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    !
                    
                      
      max_polls <- 20

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    !
                    
                      
      poll_interval <- 3

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    !
                    
                      
      for (i in seq_len(max_polls)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    !
                    
                      
          if (run_verbose) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    !
                    
                      
          cli::cli_alert("({current_index}/{total_queries}) Polling for results for job ID: {job_id} (Attempt {i}/{max_polls})")

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    
                    
                      
          }

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    !
                    
                      
        req_result <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    !
                    
                      
          httr2::request(ctx_burl) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    !
                    
                      
          httr2::req_url_path_append(path = glue::glue("chem/classyfire/{job_id}/result")) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    !
                    
                      
          httr2::req_headers("accept" = "application/json") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    !
                    
                      
          httr2::req_timeout(5) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    !
                    
                      
          httr2::req_retry(max_tries = 3, is_transient = \(resp) resp$status == 202)

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    !
                    
                      
        resp_result <- httr2::req_perform(req_result)

                    !
                    
                      
        status_code <- httr2::resp_status(resp_result)

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    
                    
                      
        # ! Temporary: print status code

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    
                    
                      
        #print(paste("Polling Status Code:", status_code))

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    !
                    
                      
        if (status_code == 200) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    !
                    
                      
          if (run_verbose) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    !
                    
                      
            cli::cli_alert_success("({current_index}/{total_queries}) Successfully retrieved result for job ID {job_id}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    
                    
                      
          }

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    !
                    
                      
          return(httr2::resp_body_json(resp_result))

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    !
                    
                      
        } else if (status_code == 202) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    !
                    
                      
          if (run_verbose) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    !
                    
                      
            cli::cli_alert(".. result not ready, waiting {poll_interval}s (Attempt {i}/{max_polls})")

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    
                    
                      
          }

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    !
                    
                      
          Sys.sleep(poll_interval)

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    !
                    
                      
        } else if (status_code == 400) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    !
                    
                      
          cli::cli_alert_danger("Bad request (400) for job ID {job_id}. The server could not understand the request.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    !
                    
                      
          return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    !
                    
                      
        } else if (status_code == 404) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    !
                    
                      
          cli::cli_alert_danger("Job ID {job_id} not found (404). It may have expired or never existed.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    !
                    
                      
          return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    !
                    
                      
        } else if (status_code == 422) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    !
                    
                      
          cli::cli_alert_danger("Unprocessable entity (422) for job ID {job_id}. The SMILES string may be invalid for classification.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    !
                    
                      
          return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    
                    
                      
        } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    !
                    
                      
          cli::cli_alert_danger("Unexpected HTTP error {status_code} when retrieving result for job ID {job_id}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    !
                    
                      
          return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    !
                    
                      
      cli::cli_alert_warning("Polling timed out after {max_polls} attempts for job ID {job_id}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    !
                    
                      
      return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    !
                    
                      
    otherwise = NA

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    
                    
                      
  # --- Map over the query ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    !
                    
                      
  results <- purrr::map(

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    !
                    
                      
    .x = query,

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    !
                    
                      
    .f = safe_classify_and_get_result,

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    !
                    
                      
    current_index = seq_along(query),

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    !
                    
                      
    total_queries = length(query),

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    !
                    
                      
    .progress = TRUE

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    !
                    
                      
  return(results)

                    		
                  

                  

                    173
                    
                    
                      
}

Compounds where the models are unable to make a predictions will be dropped as well.

ct_test <- function(query, debug = FALSE) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    !

                    !

      stringr::str_replace_all(., '\\-', '%2D') %>%

                    34
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    !

  endpoints <- list(

    'LC50', #96 hour fathead minnow

                    !

#' Cheminformatics Search

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' Searching function that interfaces with the Cheminformatics API. Sends POST request.

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @param query Takes a list of variables (such as DTXSIDs, CASRN, names, etc.) to search by.

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @param coerce Boolean variable to coerce list to a data.frame. Defaults to `FALSE`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @param searchType string

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param similarity_type string

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @param min_similarity string

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @param min_toxicity string

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @param min_auth string

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' @param hazard_name string

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' @param filter_results Boolean to restrict the data returned.

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @param filter_inc A list of feature subtypes to include. Searches by `AND` operation

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' @param element_inc A vector of elements to include.

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' @param element_exc A vector of elements to exclude, or the option of `ALL` to exclude every element EXCEPT the searched elements.

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' @param mass_type string

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' @param min_mass string

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' @param max_mass string

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' @param debug string

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ... string

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A dataframe

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
chemi_search <- function(

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
	query,

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
	searchType = c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
		"exact",

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
		"substruture",

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
		"similar",

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
		"mass",

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
		"hazard",

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
		"features"

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
	),

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
	similarity_type = c("tanimoto", "euclid", "tversky"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
	min_similarity = NULL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
	min_toxicity = c("VH", "H", "M", "L", "A"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
	min_auth = c("auth", "screen", "qsar"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
	hazard_name = c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
		"acute_oral",

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
		"acute_inhal",

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
		"acute_dermal",

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
		"cancer",

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
		"geno",

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
		"endo",

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
		"reprod",

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
		"develop",

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      
		"neuro_single",

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    
                    
                      
		"neuro_repeat",

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      
		"sys_single",

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    
                    
                      
		"sys_repeat",
