                    341
                    !
                    
                      
		trc <- df$totalRecordsCount

                    		
                  

                  

                    342
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    343
                    !
                    
                      
		df <- df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    344
                    !
                    
                      
			pluck(., 'records') %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    345
                    !
                    
                      
			map(., as_tibble) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    346
                    !
                    
                      
			list_rbind()

                    		
                  

                  

                    347
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    348
                    !
                    
                      
		if ('similarity' %in% colnames(df)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    349
                    !
                    
                      
			df <- df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    350
                    !
                    
                      
				mutate(

                    		
                  

                  

                    351
                    !
                    
                      
					relationship = case_when(

                    		
                  

                  

                    352
                    !
                    
                      
						sid == query_string ~ 'parent',

                    		
                  

                  

                    353
                    !
                    
                      
						.default = 'child'

                    		
                  

                  

                    354
                    
                    
                      
					)

                    		
                  

                  

                    355
                    
                    
                      
				)

                    		
                  

                  

                    356
                    
                    
                      
		} else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    357
                    !
                    
                      
			df

                    		
                  

                  

                    358
                    
                    
                      
		}

                    		
                  

                  

                    359
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    360
                    !
                    
                      
		cli_alert_success('{trc} compounds found!')

                    		
                  

                  

                    361
                    !
                    
                      
		return(df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    362
                    
                    
                      
	} else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    363

		cli_alert_danger("\nBad request at search!")

	}

}

#' Requests bioactivity assay data

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' @param search_type Choose from `aeid`, `spid`, `m4id`, and `dtxsid`. Defaults to `dtxsid` if not specified.

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' @param query List of variables to be queried.

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @param annotate Boolean, if `TRUE` will perform a secondary request to join the the assay details against the assay IDs.

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A data frame

                    		
                  

                  

                    8

ct_bioactivity <- function(

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
  search_type,

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
  query,

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
  annotate = FALSE

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    !
                    
                      
  query <- unique(as.vector(query))

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    !
                    
                      
  if (length(query) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_abort('Query must be a character vector.')

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    !
                    
                      
  if (missing(search_type)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_alert_warning(

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    !
                    
                      
      'No parameter specified for search type, defaulting to DTXSID!'

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    !
                    
                      
    search_type <- 'by-dtxsid'

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    !
                    
                      
    search_payload <- 'DTXSID'

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    !
                    
                      
    search_type <- match.arg(

                    !
                    
                      
      search_type,

                    32
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    !
                    
                      
    search_payload <- search_type

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    !
                    
                      
    search_type <- search_type %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    !
                    
                      
      case_when(

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    !
                    
                      
        search_type == 'aeid' ~ 'by-aeid',

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    !
                    
                      
        search_type == 'spid' ~ 'by-spid',

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    !
                    
                      
        search_type == 'm4id' ~ 'by-m4id',

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    !
                    
                      
        search_type == 'dtxsid' ~ 'by-dtxsid'

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    !
                    
                      
  run_debug <- as.logical(Sys.getenv("run_debug", "FALSE"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    !
                    
                      
  run_verbose <- as.logical(Sys.getenv("run_verbose", "FALSE"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    48

                    49
                    !

                    51

                    55
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_rule()

                    		
                  

                  

                    56

                    57

                    58
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
  # Build requests

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    !
                    
                      
  req_list <- map(

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    !
                    
                      
    query,

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    !
                    
                      
    function(query_item) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    !
                    
                      
      request(Sys.getenv('ctx_burl')) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    !
                    
                      
        req_method("GET") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    !
                    
                      
        req_url_path_append("bioactivity/data/search/") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    !
                    
                      
        req_url_path_append(search_type) %>%

                    !
                    
                      
        req_url_path_append(query_item) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    !
                    
                      
        req_headers(

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    !
                    
                      
          Accept = "application/json",

                    		
                  

                  

                    70

          `x-api-key` = ct_api_key()

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      
        )

    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    !
                    
                      
  if (run_debug) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    !
                    
                      
    return(req_list %>% pluck(., 1) %>% req_dry_run())

                    		
                  

                  

                    77

                    79
                    
                    
                      
  # Perform requests

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    !
                    
                      
  resp_list <- req_perform_sequential(req_list, on_error = 'continue', progress = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      
  # Process responses

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    !
                    
                      
  body_list <- map2(

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    !
                    
                      
    resp_list,

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    !
                    
                      
    query,

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    !
                    
                      
    function(r, query_item) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    !
                    
                      
      if (inherits(r, "httr2_error")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    !
                    
                      
        r <- r$resp

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    !
                    
                      
      if (!inherits(r, "httr2_response")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    !
                    
                      
        cli::cli_warn("Request failed for {query_item}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    !
                    
                      
        return(list())

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    !
                    
                      
      if (resp_status(r) < 200 || resp_status(r) >= 300) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    !
                    
                      
        cli::cli_warn("API request failed for {query_item} with status {resp_status(r)}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    !
                    
                      
        return(list())

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    !
                    
                      
      body <- resp_body_json(r)

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    !
                    
                      
      if (length(body) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    !
                    
                      
        return(list())

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    !
                    
                      
      return(body)

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    !
                    
                      
  df <- body_list %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    !
                    
                      
    set_names(query) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    !
                    
                      
    compact() %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    !
                    
                      
    list_rbind(names_to = "query_id")

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    !
                    
                      
  if (annotate == TRUE) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    !

                    117

                    118

                    119
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    !
                    
                      
  return(df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    
                    
                      
}

# R/ct_related.R

#' Get related substances from the EPA CompTox dashboard.

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @description

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' `r lifecycle::badge("questioning")`

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param query A character vector of DTXSIDs to query.

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @param inclusive Boolean to only return results within all of the queried compounds. Valid for over one compound.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' 

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A list of data frames containing related substances.

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' \dontrun{

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' ct_related(query = "DTXSID0024842")

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
ct_related <- function(query, inclusive = FALSE) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
  # Check if query is valid

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    !
                    
                      
  if (length(query) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_abort("Query must be a character vector of DTXSIDs.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
	# Check if query is valid for inclusion

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    !
                    
                      
	if (inclusive == TRUE & length(query) == 1) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    !
                    
                      
		cli::cli_abort("Inclusive option only valid for multiple compounds")

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
	}

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
  # Display debugging information

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    !
                    
                      
  cli::cli_rule(left = "Related substances payload options")

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    !
                    
                      
  cli::cli_dl(

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    !
                    
                      
		c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    !
                    
                      
			"Number of compounds" = "{length(query)}",

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    !
                    
                      
			"Inclusive" = "{inclusive}"

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
		)

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
	)

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    !
                    
                      
  cli::cli_rule()

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
  cli::cli_end()

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
  #TODO Remove after API endpoint comes up

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    !
                    
                      
  ctx_server(server = 9)

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
  # Helper function to fetch data safely

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    !
                    
                      
  safe_fetch <- purrr::safely(function(id) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
    #cli::cli_inform(c("v" = "Fetching related substances for DTXSID: {id}"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    
                    
                      
    # Make the request

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    !
                    
                      
    req <- request(base_url = Sys.getenv('ctx_burl')) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    !
                    
                      
      req_url_path_append('related-substances/search/by-dtxsid') %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    !
                    
                      
      req_url_query('id' = id)

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    
                    
                      
    # Dry run option

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    !
                    
                      
    if (Sys.getenv("run_debug") == "TRUE") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    !
                    
                      
      cli::cli_alert_info('DEBUGGING REQUEST')

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    !
                    
                      
      print(req)

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      
      #return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    !
                    
                      
    resp <- httr2::req_perform(req)

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    
                    
                      
    # Check the response

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    !
                    
                      
    if (httr2::resp_status(resp) != 200) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    !
                    
                      
      cli::cli_warn(

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    !
                    
                      
        "Request failed for DTXSID: {id} with status {httr2::resp_status(resp)}"

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    !
                    
                      
      return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    
                    
                      
    # Parse the JSON content

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    !
                    
                      
    httr2::resp_body_json(resp)

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      
  })

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    
                    
                      
  # Fetch data for all IDs sequentially with a progress bar

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    !
                    
                      
  results <- query %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    !
                    
                      
    purrr::map(safe_fetch, .progress = TRUE) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    !
                    
                      
    set_names(query)

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      
  # Extract the results and errors

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    !
                    
                      
  data <- purrr::map(results, "result") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    !
                    
                      
    map(., ~ pluck(., "data")) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    !
                    
                      
    map(

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    
                    
                      
      .,

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    !
                    
                      
      ~ map(

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    
                    
                      
        .,

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    !
                    
                      
        ~ keep(.x, names(.x) %in% c("dtxsid", "relationship")) %>% as_tibble()

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      
      ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    !
                    
                      
        list_rbind()

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    
                    
                      
    ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    !
                    
                      
    list_rbind(names_to = "query") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    !
                    
                      
		rename(child = dtxsid) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    
                    
                      
		#Removes parent searched compound

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    !
                    
                      
    filter(child != query)

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    !
                    
                      
  errors <- purrr::map(results, "error")

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    
                    
                      
  # Handle errors

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    !
                    
                      
  if (any(!purrr::map_lgl(errors, is.null))) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_warn(c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    !
                    
                      
      "x" = "Some requests failed:",

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    !
                    
                      
      "i" = "{sum(!purrr::map_lgl(errors, is.null))} DTXSIDs had errors."

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    
                    
                      
    ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    !
                    
                      
  ctx_server(server = 1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    !
                    
                      
if(inclusive == TRUE){

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    !
                    
                      
data <- data %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    !
                    
                      
	filter(query %in% query & child %in% query)

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    
                    
                      
}	

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    
                    
                      
  # Return the data

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    !
                    
                      
  return(data)

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
# Internal package environment for session-level caching

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
.ComptoxREnv <- new.env(parent = emptyenv())

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' First time setup for functions

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' Tests to see if APIs are up and tokens are present.

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @return Ping tests and API tokens.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
run_setup <- function() {

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    !
                    
                      
  cli::cli_rule(left = 'Ping Test for Configured Endpoints')

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
	

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    !
                    
                      
	server_urls <- c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
  # Dynamically get the list of configured server URLs. Hardcoded until health endpoints are fully up.

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    !
                    
                      
		"CompTox Dashboard API" = paste0(Sys.getenv("ctx_burl"), 'chemical/health'),

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    !
                    
                      
    "ECOTOX" = Sys.getenv("eco_burl"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    !
                    
                      
    "EPI Suite API" = 'https://episuite.dev/EpiWebSuite/#/'

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
    #,"Natural Products API" = 'https://app.naturalproducts.net/home'

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
  # Filter out any endpoints with empty/unset URLs

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    !
                    
                      
  active_endpoints <- server_urls[server_urls != "" & !is.na(server_urls)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
  # Remove entries with duplicate URLs, keeping the first name. Using `unique()` would strip the names.

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    !
                    
                      
  ping_list <- active_endpoints[!duplicated(active_endpoints)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    !
                    
                      
  if (length(ping_list) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_alert_info("No server endpoints are configured to ping.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_end()

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
    # A more informative and visually appealing check function

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    !
                    
                      
    check_url <- function(url, name) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    !
                    
                      
      tryCatch(

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
        {

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
          # Use HEAD request for efficiency; we just want to check connectivity

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    !
                    
                      
          req <- httr2::request(url) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    !
                    
                      
            httr2::req_method("HEAD") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    !
                    
                      
            httr2::req_timeout(5) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
            # Don't error on HTTP status, we check it manually

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
            httr2::req_error(is_error = \(resp) FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
          

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    !
                    
                      
          start_time <- Sys.time()

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    !
                    
                      
          resp <- httr2::req_perform(req)

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    !
                    
                      
          end_time <- Sys.time()

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
          

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    !
                    
                      
          latency <- as.numeric(difftime(end_time, start_time, units = "secs"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    !
                    
                      
          latency_fmt <- paste0(round(latency * 1000), "ms")

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    
                    
                      
          

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    !
                    
                      
          status <- httr2::resp_status(resp)

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    
                    
                      
          

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    
                    
                      
          # Use cli for styled output. 3xx redirects are not considered errors.

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
          if (status >= 200 && status < 400) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    !
                    
                      
            formatted_output <- cli::format_inline("{.strong {name}}: {cli::col_green('OK (', status, ')')} [{latency_fmt}]")

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      
          } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    !
                    
                      
            formatted_output <- cli::format_inline("{.strong {name}}: {cli::col_yellow('WARN (', status, ')')} [{latency_fmt}]")

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    
                    
                      
          }

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
        },

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    !
                    
                      
        error = function(e) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      
          # Catch httr2-specific errors for more robust error messages

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    !
                    
                      
          error_msg <- if (inherits(e, "httr2_timeout")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    !
                    
                      
            "Request timed out"

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    !
                    
                      
          } else if (inherits(e, "httr2_connect_error")){

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    !
                    
                      
            "Connection failed"

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    
                    
                      
          } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    !
                    
                      
            "Request failed" # Fallback for other errors

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    
                    
                      
          }

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    !
                    
                      
          cli::format_inline("{.strong {name}}: {cli::col_red('ERROR (', error_msg, ')')}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    !
                    
                      
		results <- purrr::imap_chr(ping_list, check_url)

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    
                    
                      
    # Check for active Cheminformatics endpoints ----

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    !
                    
                      
    tryCatch({

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    !
                    
                      
      start_time <- Sys.time()

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    !
                    
                      
      resp <- httr2::request(paste0(Sys.getenv('chemi_burl'), "/services/cim_component_info")) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    !
                    
                      
        httr2::req_perform()

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    !
                    
                      
      end_time <- Sys.time()

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    !
                    
                      
      latency <- as.numeric(difftime(end_time, start_time, units = "secs"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    !
                    
                      
      latency_fmt <- paste0(round(latency * 1000), "ms")

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    !
                    
                      
      endpoints <- resp %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    !
                    
                      
        httr2::resp_body_json() %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    !
                    
                      
        purrr::map(., ~ tibble::as_tibble(.x)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    !
                    
                      
        purrr::list_rbind() %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    !
                    
                      
				dplyr::filter(!is.na(is_available))

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    !
                    
                      
      active_chemi_endpoints <- sum(endpoints$is_available, na.rm = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    !
                    
                      
      total_chemi_endpoints <- nrow(endpoints)

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    !
                    
                      
      chemi_status <- cli::format_inline("{.strong Cheminformatics API}: {cli::col_green('OK ({active_chemi_endpoints}/{total_chemi_endpoints} endpoints active)')} [{latency_fmt}]")

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    !
                    
                      
      results <- c(results, chemi_status)

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    !
                    
                      
    }, error = function(e) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    !
                    
                      
      chemi_status <- cli::format_inline("{.strong Cheminformatics API}: {cli::col_red('ERROR (Failed to get endpoints)')}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    !
                    
                      
      results <<- c(results, chemi_status)

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_li(items = results)

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_end()

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    
                    
                      
		

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    
                    
                      
  # Token check ----

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    !
                    
                      
  cli::cli_rule(left = 'API Token Status')

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    
                    
                      
  # Directly check the environment variable to avoid aborting during package load

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    !
                    
                      
  api_key <- Sys.getenv("ctx_api_key")

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    !
                    
                      
  if (api_key == "") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_alert_warning("CompTox API Key: {.strong NOT SET}. Use {.run Sys.setenv(ctx_api_key= 'YOUR_KEY_HERE')} to set it.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_alert_success(cli::col_green("CompTox API Key: {.strong SET}."))

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    !
                    
                      
  invisible(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    122

ctx_server <- function(server = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    4x
                    
                      
	if (is.null(server)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    
                    
                      
		{

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    4x
                    
                      
			cli::cli_alert_danger("Server URL reset!")

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    4x
                    
                      
			Sys.setenv("ctx_burl" = "")

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    
                    
                      
		}

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    
                    
                      
	} else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    4x
                    
                      
		switch(

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    4x
                    
                      
			as.character(server),

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    4x
                    
                      
			"1" = Sys.setenv('ctx_burl' = 'https://comptox.epa.gov/ctx-api/'),

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    4x
                    
                      
			"2" = Sys.setenv('ctx_burl' = 'https://ctx-api-stg.ccte.epa.gov/'),

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    4x
                    
                      
			"3" = Sys.setenv('ctx_burl' = 'https://ctx-api-dev.ccte.epa.gov/'),

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    4x
                    
                      
			"5" = Sys.setenv('ctx_burl' = 'https://comptoxstaging.rtpnc.epa.gov/ctx-api/'),

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    4x
                    
                      
			"9" = Sys.setenv('ctx_burl' = 'https://comptox.epa.gov/dashboard-api/ccdapp2/'),

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    
                    
                      
			{

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    !
                    
                      
				cli::cli_alert_warning("\nInvalid server option selected!\n")

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    
                    
                      
				#cli::cli_alert_info("Valid options are 1 (Production), 2 (Staging), 3 (Development), and 9 (Scraping).")

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    !
                    
                      
				cli::cli_alert_warning("Server URL reset!")

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    !
                    
                      
				Sys.setenv("ctx_burl" = "")

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    
                    
                      
			}

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    
                    
                      
		)

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    4x
                    
                      
		Sys.getenv('ctx_burl')

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    
                    
                      
	}

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    
                    
                      
}

np_server <- function(server = NULL){

                    		
                  

                  

                    268
                    2x
                    
                      
	if (is.null(server)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    269
                    
                    
                      
		{

                    		
                  

                  

                    270
                    2x
                    
                      
			cli::cli_alert_danger("Server URL reset!")

                    		
                  

                  

                    271
                    2x
                    
                      
			Sys.setenv("np_burl" = "")

                    		
                  

                  

                    272
                    
                    
                      
		}

                    		
                  

                  

                    273
                    
                    
                      
	} else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    274
                    2x
                    
                      
		switch(

                    		
                  

                  

                    275
                    2x
                    
                      
			as.character(server),

                    		
                  

                  

                    276
                    2x
                    
                      
			"1" = Sys.setenv("np_burl" = "https://api.naturalproducts.net/latest/"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    277
                    
                    
                      
			{

#' Set verbose mode

                    		
                  

                  

                    314
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    315
                    
                    
                      
#' Sets the verbosity of the execution.

                    		
                  

                  

                    316
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    317
                    
                    
                      
#' @param verbose A logical value indicating whether verbose mode should be enabled.

                    		
                  

                  

                    318
                    
                    
                      
#'   Defaults to `FALSE`. If a non-logical value is provided, a warning is issued,

                    		
                  

                  

                    319
                    
                    
                      
#'   and verbose mode is set to `FALSE`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    320
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    321
                    
                    
                      
#' @details

                    		
                  

                  

                    322
                    
                    
                      
#' This function sets the `"run_verbose"` environment variable based on the

                    		
                  

                  

                    323
                    
                    
                      
#' `verbose` argument. If `verbose` is `TRUE`, the environment variable is set

                    		
                  

                  

                    324
                    
                    
                      
#' to `"TRUE"`. Otherwise, it is set to `"FALSE"`. If an invalid value is

                    		
                  

                  

                    325
                    
                    
                      
#' provided for `verbose`, a warning message is displayed, and the environment

                    		
                  

                  

                    326
                    
                    
                      
#' variable is set to `"FALSE"`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    327
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    328
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    329
                    
                    
                      
#' \dontrun{

                    		
                  

                  

                    330
                    
                    
                      
#' # Enable verbose mode

                    		
                  

                  

                    331
                    
                    
                      
#' run_verbose(TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    332
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    333
                    
                    
                      
#' # Disable verbose mode

                    		
                  

                  

                    334
                    
                    
                      
#' run_verbose(FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    335
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    336
                    
                    
                      
#' # Attempt to set verbose mode with an invalid value

                    		
                  

                  

                    337
                    
                    
                      
#' run_verbose("hello")

                    		
                  

                  

                    338
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    339
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    340
