                    49
                    
                    
                      
  # --- Create the request wrapper

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    
                    
                      
  # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    !
                    
                      
  safe_get_wishart_result <- purrr::possibly(

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    !
                    
                      
    .f = function(current_query, current_index, total_queries) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    !
                    
                      
      if (run_verbose) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
        cli::cli_alert_info("({current_index}/{total_queries}) Retrieving classification for InChlKey: {current_query}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    
                    
                      
      # --- Build request ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    !
                    
                      
      req <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    !
                    
                      
        httr2::request('http://classyfire.wishartlab.com/') %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    !
                    
                      
        httr2::req_url_path_append(path = glue::glue("{path}/{current_query}")) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    !
                    
                      
        httr2::req_headers(

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    !
                    
                      
          "Accept" = "application/json"

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      
        ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      
        #httr2::req_timeout(10) %>% # Increased timeout for potential large responses

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    !
                    
                      
        httr2::req_retry(

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    !
                    
                      
          retry_on_failure = TRUE # Retry on failure

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    !
                    
                      
          ,max_tries = 5,

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    
                    
                      
         # is_transient = ~ httr2::resp_is_transient(.x) || httr2::resp_status_class(.x) == "server"

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
        )

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      
      # --- Handle debug mode (dry run) ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    !
                    
                      
      if (run_debug) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    !
                    
                      
        cli::cli_alert_info("Dry run for request:")

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    !
                    
                      
        httr2::req_dry_run(req)

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    !
                    
                      
        return(invisible(req)) # Return the request object in debug mode

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
      # --- Perform request ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    !
                    
                      
      resp <- httr2::req_perform(req)

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      
      # --- Validate response ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    !
                    
                      
      if (httr2::resp_is_error(resp)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    !
                    
                      
        status_code <- httr2::resp_status(resp)

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    !
                    
                      
        cli::cli_alert_danger("({current_index}/{total_queries}) HTTP error {status_code} for InChlKey: {current_query}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    !
                    
                      
        cli::cli_alert_info("Response body: {.val {httr2::resp_body_string(resp)}}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    !
                    
                      
        return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    !
                    
                      
      if (run_verbose) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    !
                    
                      
        cli::cli_alert_success("({current_index}/{total_queries}) Successfully retrieved result for InChlKey: {current_query}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    !
                    
                      
      httr2::resp_body_json(resp)

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    
                    
                      
    },

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    !
                    
                      
    otherwise = NA # Return NA for any unexpected R errors

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    
                    
                      
  # --- Map over the query ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    !
                    
                      
  results <- purrr::map(

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    !
                    
                      
    .x = query,

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    !
                    
                      
    .f = safe_get_wishart_result,

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    !
                    
                      
    current_index = seq_along(query),

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    !
                    
                      
    total_queries = length(query),

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    !
                    
                      
    .progress = TRUE

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    !
                    
                      
  return(results)

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Safety + GHS data from Cheminformatics

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' @description

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' Returns a data frame that contains a binned comparison table generated from the GHS codes and the NFPA 704 'safety diamond'

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @param query A list of DTXSIDs to search for

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A list of data

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' \dontrun{

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' chemi_safety(query = "DTXSID7020182")

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
chemi_safety <- function(query) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
  # Request standardized via generic_chemi_request

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    !
                    
                      
  df_raw <- generic_chemi_request(

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    !
                    
                      
    query = query,

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    !
                    
                      
    endpoint = "safety",

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    !
                    
                      
    server = 'chemi_burl',

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    !
                    
                      
    wrap = FALSE

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    !
                    
                      
  if (nrow(df_raw) == 0) return(invisible(NULL))

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
  # Tidy up headers early using vectorized logic

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    !
                    
                      
  headers <- df_raw %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::filter(!purrr::map_lgl(chemical, is.null)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::select(dtxsid = sid, chemical) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    !
                    
                      
    tidyr::unnest_wider(chemical) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::select(dplyr::any_of(c("name", "dtxsid")))

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
  # Extract flags into a long-format dataframe for cleaner processing

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    !
                    
                      
  flags_long <- df_raw %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::select(dtxsid, flags) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    !
                    
                      
    tidyr::unnest_wider(flags)

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
  # --- Optimized NFPA Decoding ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    !
                    
                      
  nfpa <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
  if ("NFPA" %in% colnames(flags_long)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
    # Static mapping for NFPA codes to bins

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    !
                    
                      
    nfpa_bin_map <- c("1" = "L", "2" = "M", "3" = "H", "4" = "VH", "0" = "I")

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    !
                    
                      
    nfpa <- flags_long %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::select(dtxsid, NFPA) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    !
                    
                      
      tidyr::unnest(NFPA) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    !
                    
                      
      tidyr::unnest(NFPA) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::mutate(

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    !
                    
                      
        nfpa_health = stringr::str_sub(NFPA, 1, 1),

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    !
                    
                      
        nfpa_fire = stringr::str_sub(NFPA, 2, 2),

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    !
                    
                      
        nfpa_stability = stringr::str_sub(NFPA, 3, 3),

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
        nfpa_special = stringr::str_sub(NFPA, 4, -1),

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    
                    
                      
        # Vectorized lookup instead of case_when

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    !
                    
                      
        health_bin = nfpa_bin_map[nfpa_health],

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    !
                    
                      
        fire_bin = nfpa_bin_map[nfpa_fire],

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    !
                    
                      
        stability_bin = nfpa_bin_map[nfpa_stability],

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    !
                    
                      
        special_bin = dplyr::if_else(!stringr::str_detect(nfpa_special, "\\S"), NA_character_, nfpa_special)

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      
      ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::select(-NFPA, -dplyr::starts_with("nfpa_")) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    !
                    
                      
      tidyr::pivot_longer(

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    !
                    
                      
        cols = health_bin:special_bin,

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    !
                    
                      
        values_to = "bin",

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    !
                    
                      
        names_to = "hazard_class",

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    !
                    
                      
        values_drop_na = TRUE

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    
                    
                      
      ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::mutate(

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
        # Handle special VH overrides for oxidizing/water-reactive

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    !
                    
                      
        bin = dplyr::case_when(

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    !
                    
                      
          bin %in% c("OX", "W") ~ "VH",

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    !
                    
                      
          .default = bin

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    
                    
                      
        )

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    
                    
                      
  # --- Optimized GHS Mapping ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    !
                    
                      
  ghs_codes <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    !
                    
                      
  if ("GHS Codes" %in% colnames(flags_long)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    !
                    
                      
    ghs_tbl <- ghs_create_tbl() # Uses session cache internally

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    !
                    
                      
    ghs_codes <- flags_long %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::select(dtxsid, `GHS Codes`) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    !
                    
                      
      tidyr::unnest_longer(`GHS Codes`) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::rename(h_code = `GHS Codes`) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    
                    
                      
      # Fast join against the GHS dictionary

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::inner_join(ghs_tbl, by = "h_code")

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      
  # --- Physical Hazards Summary Merging ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    !
                    
                      
  final_df <- dplyr::bind_rows(nfpa, ghs_codes) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::filter(hazard_class != "health_bin") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::mutate(

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    
                    
                      
      # Grouping endpoints into logical classes

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    !
                    
                      
      class = dplyr::case_when(

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    !
                    
                      
        hazard_class %in% c("stability_bin", "Desensitized explosives", "Explosives") ~ "Explosives",

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    !
                    
                      
        hazard_class %in% c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    !
                    
                      
          "fire_bin", "Flammable gases", "Flammable liquids", "Flammable solids", 

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    !
                    
                      
          "Pyrophoric solids", "Pyrophoric liquids", "Substances and mixtures which in contact with water, emit flammable gases",

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    !
                    
                      
          "Self-heating substances and mixtures"

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    !
                    
                      
        ) ~ "Flammable",

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    !
                    
                      
        hazard_class %in% c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    !
                    
                      
          "Oxidizing gases", "Oxidizing liquids; Oxidizing solids", "Self-reactive substances and mixtures; Organic peroxides"

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    !
                    
                      
        ) ~ "Oxidizers/ Self-Rxn",

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    !
                    
                      
        hazard_class %in% c("Gases under pressure", "Chemicals under pressure", "Aerosols") ~ "Pressurized chemicals",

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    !
                    
                      
        hazard_class %in% c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    !
                    
                      
          "Corrosive to Metals", "Skin corrosion/irritation and serious eye damage/eye irritation", 

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    !
                    
                      
          "Skin corrosion/irritation", "Serious eye damage/eye irritation"

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    !
                    
                      
        ) ~ "Corrosive",

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    !
                    
                      
        hazard_class == "Hazardous to the ozone layer" ~ "Ozone-depleting",

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    !
                    
                      
        .default = hazard_class

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    
                    
                      
      ),

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    !
                    
                      
      bin = factor(bin, levels = c("VH", "H", "M", "L", "I", "ND", NA)),

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    
                    
                      
    ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::arrange(bin) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::distinct(dtxsid, class, .keep_all = TRUE) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    !
                    
                      
    tidyr::pivot_wider(

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    !
                    
                      
      id_cols = dtxsid,

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    !
                    
                      
      names_from = class,

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    !
                    
                      
      values_from = bin,

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    !
                    
                      
      values_fill = NA

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    
                    
                      
  # Final summary counts using rowSums (vectorized) instead of rowwise()

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    !
                    
                      
  final_df <- final_df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::mutate(n = rowSums(!is.na(dplyr::across(-dtxsid)))) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::arrange(dplyr::desc(n)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::inner_join(headers, by = "dtxsid") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::relocate(name, .before = dtxsid)

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    !
                    
                      
  return(final_df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    
                    
                      
}

#' Optimized GHS Table Creation with Session Caching

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    
                    
                      
#' @return Data frame

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    
                    
                      
ghs_create_tbl <- function() {

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    
                    
                      
  # Check if table is already in session cache

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    !
                    
                      
  if (!is.null(.ComptoxREnv$ghs_table)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    !
                    
                      
    return(.ComptoxREnv$ghs_table)

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    !
                    
                      
  url <- "https://pubchem.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/ghs/ghscode_10.txt"

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    !
                    
                      
  lines <- tryCatch(readLines(url, warn = FALSE), error = function(e) return(NULL))

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    !
                    
                      
  if (is.null(lines)) return(tibble::tibble())

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    !
                    
                      
  split_lines <- purrr::map(strsplit(lines, "\t"), ~ .x[-8])

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    
                    
                      
  # Header is actually H-Code, Statement, Class, Category, UN, Pictogram, Signal

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    
                    
                      
  # We only need H-Code and the bin logic.

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    !
                    
                      
  df <- as.data.frame(do.call(rbind, split_lines[-1]), stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    !
                    
                      
  colnames(df) <- split_lines[[1]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    
                    
                      
  # Unified binning logic

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    !
                    
                      
  res <- df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::filter(stringr::str_detect(`H-Code`, pattern = "H")) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::mutate(

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    !
                    
                      
      bin = dplyr::case_when(

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    !
                    
                      
        `H-Code` %in% c("H222", "H229", "H304", "H282", "H314", "H318", "H315+H320", "H220", "H221", "H230", "H231", "H232", "H224", "H225", "H228", "H270", "H271", "H272", "H250", "H251") ~ "VH",

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    !
                    
                      
        `H-Code` %in% c("H240", "H241", "H242", "H260", "H261", "H200", "H201", "H202", "H203", "H205", "H209", "H210", "H211", "H206", "H207") ~ "VH",

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    !
                    
                      
        `H-Code` %in% c("H223", "H305", "H283", "H284", "H290", "H204", "H208", "H226", "H227", "H280", "H281", "H420", "H252") ~ "H",

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    !
                    
                      
        `H-Code` %in% c("H315", "H319") ~ "M",

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    !
                    
                      
        `H-Code` %in% c("H316", "H320") ~ "L",

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    !
                    
                      
        `H-Code` == "-" ~ "I",

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    !
                    
                      
        .default = "MISSING"

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    
                    
                      
    ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::filter(bin != "MISSING") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::select(h_code = `H-Code`, hazard_class = `Hazard Class`, bin) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::distinct(h_code, bin, .keep_all = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    173
                    
                    
                      
  # Cache the result for the remainder of the session

                    		
                  

                  

                    174
                    !
                    
                      
  .ComptoxREnv$ghs_table <- res

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    176
                    !
                    
                      
  return(res)

                    		
                  

                  

                    177
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Predict properties of chemical compounds using an external API.

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' This function takes a vector of chemical identifiers as input, resolves them

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' using `chemi_resolver`, and then uses an external API to predict their properties.

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' It sends a POST request to the API endpoint, passing the resolved chemical names

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' in the request body.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param query A character vector of chemical identifiers to predict properties for.

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @param report A character string specifying the report format. Must be one of

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#'   "UNKNOWN", "SDF", "SMI", "MOL", "CSV", "TSV", "JSON", "XLSX", "PDF", "HTML",

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#'   "XML", or "DOCX". Defaults to "JSON".

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A list containing the API response.  Returns NULL if the

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#'   API returns no results for a given query.

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' \dontrun{

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' # Example usage with a single identifier:

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' predicted_properties <- chemi_predict(c("aspirin"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' print(predicted_properties)

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' # Example usage with multiple identifiers:

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#' predicted_properties <- chemi_predict(c("aspirin", "ibuprofen", "water"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#' print(predicted_properties)

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
chemi_predict <- function(query, report = "JSON") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
  # Check if the query is missing. If so, abort with an error message.

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    !
                    
                      
  if (is.null(query) | missing(query)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_abort('Request missing')

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
  # Resolve chemical identifiers using chemi_resolver

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    !
                    
                      
  resolved_chemicals <- chemi_resolver(query)

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
  # Check if chemi_resolver returned any results

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    !
                    
                      
  if (length(resolved_chemicals) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_abort("No chemicals resolved for the given query.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    !
                    
                      
    return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
  # Validate the report parameter

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    !
                    
                      
  allowed_reports <- c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    !
                    
                      
    "SDF",

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    !
                    
                      
    "SMI",

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    !
                    
                      
    "MOL",

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    !
                    
                      
    "CSV",

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    !
                    
                      
    "TSV",

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    !
                    
                      
    "JSON",

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    !
                    
                      
    "XLSX",

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    !
                    
                      
    "PDF",

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    !
                    
                      
    "HTML",

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    !
                    
                      
    "XML",

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
    "DOCX"

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    !
                    
                      
  if (!(report %in% allowed_reports)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_warn(paste0(

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    !
                    
                      
      "Invalid report format '",

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    !
                    
                      
      report,

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    !
                    
                      
      "'. Defaulting to JSON."

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      
    ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    !
                    
                      
    report <- "JSON"

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    
                    
                      
  # Display information about the prediction request.

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    !
                    
                      
  cli_rule(left = "Prediction request")

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    !
                    
                      
  cli_dl(

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    !
                    
                      
    c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    !
                    
                      
      "Number of compounds" = "{length(resolved_chemicals)}",

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    !
                    
                      
      "Report format" = "{report}"

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    !
                    
                      
  cli_rule()

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    !
                    
                      
  cli_end()

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    !
                    
                      
  resp <- request(Sys.getenv('chemi_burl')) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    !
                    
                      
    req_method("POST") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    !
                    
                      
    req_url_path_append("webtest/predict") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    !
                    
                      
    req_headers(Accept = "application/json, text/plain, */*") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    !
                    
                      
    req_body_json(

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    !
                    
                      
      list(structures = resolved_chemicals, report = report),

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    !
                    
                      
      auto_unbox = TRUE

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    
                    
                      
    ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    !
                    
                      
    req_perform()

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    !
                    
                      
  if (resp_status(resp) >= 400) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_abort(paste("API request failed with status", resp_status(resp)))

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    !
                    
                      
  resp_body_json(resp)

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Retrieves compound physio-chem properties by DTXSID

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' Returns both experimental and predicted results.

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @details

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' For a full list of properties that can be searched for, load the data set `property_ids` and use the `propertyId` field for the `query` field.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param search_param Search for `compound` or `property` to look for.

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @param query A list of DTXSIDs or a property to be queries against. See details for full list of properties available.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @param range A lower and upper range of values to search for if a property was specified for.

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @param coerce Boolean to coerce data to a list of data frames

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A list or dataframe

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
ct_properties <- function(

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
  search_param,

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
  query,

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
  range,

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
  coerce = TRUE

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    !
                    
                      
  if (missing(search_param)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_abort("Missing search type!")

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    !
                    
                      
  if (search_param == "compound") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    !
                    
                      
    df <- generic_request(

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    !
                    
                      
      query = query,

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    !
                    
                      
      endpoint = "chemical/property/search/by-dtxsid/",

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    !
                    
                      
      method = "POST",

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    !
                    
                      
      batch_limit = 200

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    !
                    
                      
    if (coerce == TRUE && nrow(df) > 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    !
                    
                      
      df <- df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    !
                    
                      
        split(.$propertyId)

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    !
                    
                      
    return(df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    !
                    
                      
  if (search_param == "property") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
    if (missing(range) || length(range) != 2) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    !
                    
                      
      cli::cli_abort("Missing range for property search! Range must be a vector of length 2.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    !
                    
                      
    range <- as.numeric(range)

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    !
                    
                      
    run_debug <- as.logical(Sys.getenv("run_debug", "FALSE"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    !
                    
                      
    run_verbose <- as.logical(Sys.getenv("run_verbose", "FALSE"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    !
                    
                      
    if (run_verbose) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    !
                    
                      
      cli::cli_rule(left = "Phys-chem properties payload options")

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    !
                    
                      
      cli::cli_dl(

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    !
                    
                      
        c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
          "Search type" = "{search_param}",

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    !
                    
                      
          "Property" = "{query}",

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    !
                    
                      
          "Range" = "{paste(range, collapse = '-')}",

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    !
                    
                      
          "Coerce" = "{coerce}"

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    
                    
                      
        )

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    !
                    
                      
      cli::cli_rule()

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    !
                    
                      
      cli::cli_end()

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      
    # Build request for range search

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    !
                    
                      
    req <- request(Sys.getenv('ctx_burl')) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    !
                    
                      
      req_method("GET") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    !
                    
                      
      req_url_path_append("chemical/property/search/by-range/") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    !
                    
                      
      req_url_path_append(query) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    !
                    
                      
      req_url_path_append(as.character(range[1])) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    !
                    
                      
      req_url_path_append(as.character(range[2])) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    !
                    
                      
      req_headers(

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    !
                    
                      
        Accept = "application/json",

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    !
                    
                      
        `x-api-key` = ct_api_key()

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    !
                    
                      
    if (run_debug) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    !
                    
                      
      return(req_dry_run(req))

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    !
                    
                      
    resp <- req_perform(req)

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    !
                    
                      
    if (resp_status(resp) < 200 || resp_status(resp) >= 300) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    !
                    
                      
      cli::cli_abort("API request failed with status {resp_status(resp)}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    !
                    
                      
    body <- resp_body_json(resp)

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    !
                    
                      
    if (length(body) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    !
                    
                      
      return(tibble())

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    !
                    
                      
    df <- body %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    !
                    
                      
      map(~ map_if(.x, is.null, ~NA_character_)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    !
                    
                      
      as_tibble()

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    !
                    
                      
    return(df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    !
                    
                      
  cli::cli_abort("search_param must be either 'compound' or 'property'")

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    
                    
                      
#' Get property IDs for property searching

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    
                    
                      
#'
