                    105
                    
                    
                      
.prop_ids <- function() {

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    
                    
                      
  # Predicted properties

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    !
                    
                      
  req_pred <- request("https://api-ccte.epa.gov") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    !
                    
                      
    req_method("GET") %>%

                    !

                    !

                    !
                    
                      
      Accept = "application/json",

      `x-api-key` = ct_api_key()

    )

  resp_pred <- req_perform(req_pred)

  if (resp_status(resp_pred) < 200 || resp_status(resp_pred) >= 300) {

                    121
                    !
                    
                      
  pred <- resp_body_json(resp_pred) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    !
                    
                      
    map(~ map_if(.x, is.null, ~NA_character_)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    !
                    
                      
    as_tibble()

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    
                    
                      
  # Experimental properties

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    !
                    
                      
  req_exp <- request("https://api-ccte.epa.gov") %>%

                    !
                    
                      
    req_method("GET") %>%

#' @title Clean Unicode symbols in character strings

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' @description A function to replace Unicode symbols (Greek letters, math symbols, etc.)

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' with their ASCII equivalents or pseudo-delimited names.

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @param x A character vector or a data frame to be processed.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ... Additional arguments passed to methods.

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @return The modified character vector or data frame.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' @details

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' Greek letters are replaced with lowercase labels surrounded by periods (e.g., '.alpha.').

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' Mathematical symbols like '' are replaced with '>=' and '' with '+/-'.

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' If a data frame is provided, all character columns are processed.

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' Unhandled Unicode characters will be flagged for the user.

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' \dontrun{

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#' clean_unicode("17-Estradiol")

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' # Returns: "17.beta.-Estradiol"

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#' clean_unicode("Concentration  10 g/L")

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#' # Returns: "Concentration >= 10 u g/L"

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom stringi stri_replace_all_fixed stri_escape_unicode

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom cli cli_alert_warning cli_bullets cli_alert_info

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom dplyr mutate across where

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom stringr str_extract_all

#' @importFrom magrittr %>%

clean_unicode.character <- function(x, ...) {

                    42
                    11x
                    
                      
  if (!exists("unicode_map")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
    # Fallback if internal data is not loaded (e.g. during development if not using load_all)

                    !

                    45
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    47

                    11x

                    57
                    11x

                    58
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    59

#' Internal function to check for unhandled unicode

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    
                    
                      
#' @param x Character vector

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    
                    
                      
#' @keywords internal

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      
check_unhandled <- function(x) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      
  # Avoid processing NA

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    1x
                    
                      
  if (all(is.na(x))) return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    
                    
                      
  # Escape to find \uXXXX patterns

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    
                    
                      
  # We use na.omit to avoid issues with escaped NA strings

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    10x
                    
                      
  escaped <- stringi::stri_escape_unicode(stats::na.omit(x))

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    
                    
                      
  # Find patterns like \u03b1 or \U00000000

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    10x
                    
                      
  unhandled <- unique(unlist(stringr::str_extract_all(escaped, "\\\\[uU][0-9a-fA-F]{4,8}")))

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    
                    
                      
  # Filter out some common escaped characters that are NOT symbols if any (usually none in stri_escape_unicode)

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    10x
                    
                      
  if (length(unhandled) > 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    1x
                    
                      
    cli::cli_warn("{length(unhandled)} unhandled Unicode symbol(s) detected:")

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    1x
                    
                      
    cli::cli_bullets(setNames(unhandled, rep("*", length(unhandled))))

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    1x
                    
                      
    cli::cli_alert_info("Consider updating data-raw/unicode_map.R to include these.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    
                    
                      
}

#' Optimized Hazard Comparison

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      
#' @description

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      
#' Retrieves records for queried compounds. Generates a list containing headers,

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    
                    
                      
#' raw long-form data, binned scores, and (optionally) coerced numerical records.

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    
                    
                      
#' @param query A list of DTXSIDS to search for.

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    
                    
                      
#' @param analogs String of variables to search for. Defaults to no analogs.

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    
                    
                      
#' @param min_sim Tanimoto similarity coefficient. Defaults to `0.8`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    
                    
                      
#' @param coerce Choice of `simple`, `bin`, or `numerical`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A list of dataframes

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    
                    
                      
chemi_hazard <- function(

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    
                    
                      
  query,

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    
                    
                      
  analogs = c('substructure', 'similar', 'toxprint'),

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    
                    
                      
  min_sim = NULL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    
                    
                      
  coerce = c('simple', 'bin', 'numerical')

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    
                    
                      
) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    
                    
                      
  # --- 1. Setup & Request ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    !
                    
                      
  analogs <- if (missing(analogs)) NULL else rlang::arg_match(analogs)

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    !
                    
                      
  if (!is.null(analogs)) analogs <- stringr::str_to_upper(analogs)

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    !
                    
                      
  min_sim <- if (!is.null(analogs) && !is.null(min_sim)) as.character(min_sim) else '0.8'

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    !
                    
                      
  coerce <- rlang::arg_match(coerce)

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    !
                    
                      
  df_raw <- generic_chemi_request(

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    !
                    
                      
    query = query,

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    !
                    
                      
    endpoint = "hazard",

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    !
                    
                      
    options = list(minSimilarity = min_sim, analogSearchType = analogs),

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    !
                    
                      
    server = "chemi_burl",

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    !
                    
                      
    tidy = FALSE # Maintain list structure for deep cleaning

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    !
                    
                      
  if (is.null(df_raw) || length(df_raw) == 0) return(invisible(NULL))

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    
                    
                      
  # --- 2. Unified Long-Format Extraction ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    
                    
                      
  # Pivot to tidy long format as early as possible to vectorize logic

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    !
                    
                      
  hazard_chemicals <- purrr::pluck(df_raw, "hazardChemicals")

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    
                    
                      
  # Standardize headers

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    !
                    
                      
  headers <- purrr::map_dfr(hazard_chemicals, ~ {

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    !
                    
                      
    c <- purrr::pluck(.x, "chemical")

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    !
                    
                      
    tibble::tibble(dtxsid = c$sid, name = c$name)

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    !
                    
                      
  }) %>% dplyr::distinct()

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    
                    
                      
  # Standardize all scores into a unified long tidy tibble

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    !
                    
                      
  long_data <- purrr::map_dfr(hazard_chemicals, function(chem_entry) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    !
                    
                      
    sid <- purrr::pluck(chem_entry, "chemical", "sid")

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    !
                    
                      
    scores <- purrr::pluck(chem_entry, "scores")

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    !
                    
                      
    purrr::map_dfr(scores, function(s) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    !
                    
                      
      records <- purrr::pluck(s, "records")

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    
                    
                      
      # Extract core record data (taking first record or NA if empty)

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    !
                    
                      
      rec_data <- if (length(records) > 0) records[[1]] else list()

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    !
                    
                      
      tibble::as_tibble(purrr::compact(list(

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    !
                    
                      
        dtxsid = sid,

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    !
                    
                      
        hazardId = s$hazardId,

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    !
                    
                      
        finalScore = s$finalScore,

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    !
                    
                      
        finalAuthority = s$finalAuthority,

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    !
                    
                      
        hazardCode = rec_data$hazardCode,

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    !
                    
                      
        valueMass = rec_data$valueMass,

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    !
                    
                      
        source = rec_data$source,

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    !
                    
                      
        rationale = rec_data$rationale

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    
                    
                      
      )))

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      
  })

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    
                    
                      
  # --- 3. Binning & Display Logic ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    
                    
                      
  # Define static order for consistent rendering

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    !
                    
                      
  endpoint_order <- c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    !
                    
                      
    "acuteMammalianOral", "acuteMammalianDermal", "acuteMammalianInhalation",

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    !
                    
                      
    "developmental", "reproductive", "endocrine", "genotoxicity", "carcinogenicity",

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    !
                    
                      
    "neurotoxicitySingle", "neurotoxicityRepeat", "systemicToxicitySingle", "systemicToxicityRepeat",

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    !
                    
                      
    "eyeIrritation", "skinIrritation", "skinSensitization", "acuteAquatic", "chronicAquatic",

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    !
                    
                      
    "persistence", "bioaccumulation", "exposure"

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    !
                    
                      
  processed_data <- long_data %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::mutate(

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    !
                    
                      
      hazardId = factor(hazardId, levels = endpoint_order),

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    
                    
                      
      # Add styling for displays

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    !
                    
                      
      display_score = dplyr::case_when(

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    !
                    
                      
        finalAuthority == 'Authoritative' ~ paste0('<b>', finalScore, '</b>'),

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    !
                    
                      
        finalAuthority == 'QSAR Model' ~ paste0('<i>', finalScore, '</i>'),

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    !
                    
                      
        .default = finalScore

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    
                    
                      
    ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::arrange(hazardId, factor(finalScore, levels = c('VH', 'H', 'M', 'L', 'I', 'ND', NA))) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    !
                    
                      
    dplyr::distinct(dtxsid, hazardId, .keep_all = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    
                    
                      
  # --- 4. Coercion Branch Logic (Optimized) ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    !
                    
                      
  coerced_records <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    173
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    174
                    !
                    
                      
  if (coerce == "simple") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    !
                    
                      
    score_map <- c('VH' = 5, 'H' = 4, 'M' = 3, 'L' = 2, 'I' = 1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    176
                    !
                    
                      
    coerced_records <- processed_data %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    177
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::mutate(amount = score_map[finalScore]) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    178
                    !
                    
                      
      tidyr::pivot_wider(id_cols = dtxsid, names_from = hazardId, values_from = amount)

                    		
                  

                  

                    179
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    !
                    
                      
  } else if (coerce == "bin") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    !
                    
                      
    auth_map <- c('Authoritative' = 0, 'Screening' = 1/3, 'QSAR Model' = 2/3)

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    !
                    
                      
    score_map <- c('VH' = 5, 'H' = 4, 'M' = 3, 'L' = 2, 'I' = 1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    !
                    
                      
    coerced_records <- processed_data %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    184
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::mutate(

                    		
                  

                  

                    185
                    !
                    
                      
        val = score_map[finalScore],

                    		
                  

                  

                    186
                    !
                    
                      
        penalty = dplyr::coalesce(auth_map[finalAuthority], 0),

                    		
                  

                  

                    187
                    !
                    
                      
        amount = val - penalty

                    		
                  

                  

                    188
                    
                    
                      
      ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    189
                    !
                    
                      
      tidyr::pivot_wider(id_cols = dtxsid, names_from = hazardId, values_from = amount)

                    		
                  

                  

                    190
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    191
                    !
                    
                      
  } else if (coerce == "numerical") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    192
                    
                    
                      
    # Optimized lookup join instead of sequential str_detect

                    		
                  

                  

                    193
                    !
                    
                      
    scoring_matrix <- get_hazard_scoring_matrix()

                    		
                  

                  

                    194
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    195
                    
                    
                      
    # 1. First, handle explicit valueMass data

                    		
                  

                  

                    196
                    !
                    
                      
    num_data <- processed_data %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    197
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::filter(!finalScore %in% c("ND", "I") & !is.null(valueMass)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    198
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::mutate(

                    		
                  

                  

                    199
                    !
                    
                      
        amount = valueMass,

                    		
                  

                  

                    200
                    !
                    
                      
        invert = hazardId %in% c('persistence', 'acuteMammalianOral', 'acuteMammalianDermal', 'acuteMammalianInhalation', 'acuteAquatic', 'chronicAquatic')

                    		
                  

                  

                    201
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    202
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    203
                    
                    
                      
    # 2. Join against Scoring Matrix for categorical overrides

                    		
                  

                  

                    204
                    !
                    
                      
    cat_data <- processed_data %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    205
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::left_join(scoring_matrix, by = c("hazardId" = "endpoint", "finalScore")) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    206
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::filter(!is.na(amount))

                    		
                  

                  

                    207
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    208
                    
                    
                      
    # 3. Clean and Invert

                    		
                  

                  

                    209
                    !
                    
                      
    coerced_records <- dplyr::bind_rows(num_data, cat_data) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    210
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::mutate(amount = dplyr::if_else(dplyr::coalesce(invert_flag, FALSE), 1/amount, amount)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    211
                    !
                    
                      
      tidyr::pivot_wider(id_cols = dtxsid, names_from = hazardId, values_from = amount)

                    		
                  

                  

                    212
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    213
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    214
                    
                    
                      
  # --- 5. Assemble Result List ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    215
                    !
                    
                      
  results <- list(

                    		
                  

                  

                    216
                    !
                    
                      
    headers = headers,

                    		
                  

                  

                    217
                    !
                    
                      
    data = processed_data %>% dplyr::select(dtxsid, hazardId, finalAuthority, finalScore),

                    		
                  

                  

                    218
                    !
                    
                      
    score = processed_data %>% tidyr::pivot_wider(id_cols = dtxsid, names_from = hazardId, values_from = finalScore),

                    		
                  

                  

                    219
                    !
                    
                      
    display_table = processed_data %>% tidyr::pivot_wider(id_cols = dtxsid, names_from = hazardId, values_from = display_score),

                    		
                  

                  

                    220
                    !
                    
                      
    records = coerced_records

                    		
                  

                  

                    221
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    222
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    223
                    !
                    
                      
  return(results)

                    		
                  

                  

                    224
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Search for synonyms by DTXSID

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' @param query Vector of DTXSIDs (strings).

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' @param request_method String: 'GET' or 'POST'. Defaults to 'GET'.

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @details This function checks the `run_debug` environment variable, which can be

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' set with `run_debug()`. If `TRUE`, it will perform a dry run and return the

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' request objects instead of executing them.

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @returns A data frame of synonym results.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
ct_synonym <- function(query, request_method = "GET") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
	# 1. Input validation and setup ------

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    !
                    
                      
	query_vector <- unique(as.vector(query))

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    !
                    
                      
	request_method <- rlang::arg_match(request_method, values = c("GET", "POST"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
	# Informative CLI output -----

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    !
                    
                      
	cli::cli_rule(left = 'Synonym search options')

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    !
                    
                      
	cli::cli_dl(

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    !
                    
                      
		items = c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    !
                    
                      
			'Compound count' = "{length(query_vector)}",

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    !
                    
                      
			'Request method' = "{request_method}"

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
		)

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
	)

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    !
                    
                      
	cli::cli_end()

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    !
                    
                      
	cli::cat_line()

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
	# Build list of requests -----------------------------------------------------------------

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    !
                    
                      
	base_req <- httr2::request(Sys.getenv('ctx_burl')) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    !
                    
                      
		httr2::req_headers(

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    !
                    
                      
			accept = "application/json",

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    !
                    
                      
			`x-api-key` = ct_api_key()

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
		) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    !
                    
                      
		httr2::req_url_path("/chemical/synonym/search/by-dtxsid/")

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
	## GET requests ------

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    !
                    
                      
	if (request_method == "GET") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    !
                    
                      
		reqs <- purrr::map(

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    !
                    
                      
			stats::setNames(query_vector, query_vector),

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    !
                    
                      
			function(dtxsid) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    !
                    
                      
				base_req %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
					httr2::req_method("GET") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    !
                    
                      
					httr2::req_url_path_append(dtxsid)

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
			}

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
		)

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
	}

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
	## POST requests ------

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    !
                    
                      
	if (request_method == "POST") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      
		# Split queries into chunks of 100

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    
                    
                      
		# ! NOTE: Documentation site usually says 200, other endpoints have been discovered to be ~100

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    !
                    
                      
		query_chunks <- split(

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
			query_vector,

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    !
                    
                      
			ceiling(seq_along(query_vector) / 100)

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      
		)

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    !
                    
                      
		reqs <- purrr::map(query_chunks, function(chunk) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    !
                    
                      
			base_req %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    !
                    
                      
				httr2::req_method("POST") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    !
                    
                      
				httr2::req_body_json(data = chunk, auto_unbox = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    
                    
                      
		})

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      
	}

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    
                    
                      
	# Dry run ----

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    !
                    
                      
	if (isTRUE(as.logical(Sys.getenv('run_debug')))) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    !
                    
                      
		return(purrr::map(reqs, httr2::req_dry_run))

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
	}

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      
	# Send requests ----

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    !
                    
                      
	resps <- httr2::req_perform_sequential(

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    !
                    
                      
		reqs,

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    !
                    
                      
		on_error = 'continue',

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    !
                    
                      
		progress = TRUE

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    
                    
                      
	)

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
	# GET response parsing ----

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    !
                    
                      
	if (request_method == "GET") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    !
                    
                      
		resps <- set_names(resps, names(reqs))

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      
		# Process all responses, creating a row of NAs for failed/empty ones.

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    !
                    
                      
		results <- purrr::map(resps, function(resp) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    
                    
                      
			# `resp` from req_perform_sequential can be a response, an error, or NULL.

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    
                    
                      
			# If it's an httr2 error condition, extract the response object from it.

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    !
                    
                      
			if (inherits(resp, "httr2_error")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    !
                    
                      
				resp <- resp$resp

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    
                    
                      
			}

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      
			# Handle cases where the request failed completely (e.g., timeout) or

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    
                    
                      
			# where `resp` was an error condition without a response object.

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    !
                    
                      
			if (!inherits(resp, "httr2_response")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    !
                    
                      
				msg <- if (is.null(resp)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    !
                    
                      
					"No response received from server."

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    
                    
                      
				} else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    !
                    
                      
					as.character(resp)

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    
                    
                      
				}

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    !
                    
                      
				cli::cli_warn("A request failed: {msg}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    !
                    
                      
				return(tibble::tibble(error = "Request failed", message = msg))

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    
                    
                      
			}

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    !
                    
                      
			status <- httr2::resp_status(resp)

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    
                    
                      
			# ! 2xx: Success

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    !
                    
                      
			if (status < 300) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    !
                    
                      
				body <- httr2::resp_body_json(resp)

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    !
                    
                      
				if (length(body) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    !
                    
                      
					return(tibble::tibble()) # No results found, return empty tibble

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    
                    
                      
				}

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    
                    
                      
				# Process body like a successful response

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    !
                    
                      
				return(

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    !
                    
                      
					body %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    !
                    
                      
						purrr::discard(., names(.) %in% c('pcCode', 'dtxsid')) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    !
                    
                      
						purrr::map(

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    
                    
                      
							.,

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    
                    
                      
							~ {

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    
                    
                      
								#inner list parsing

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    !
                    
                      
								purrr::map_if(.x, is.null, ~NA_character_)

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    
                    
                      
							}

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    
                    
                      
						) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    !
                    
                      
						compact() %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    !
                    
                      
						map(., list_c) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    !
                    
                      
						map(., as_tibble) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    !
                    
                      
						list_rbind(names_to = 'quality')

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    
                    
                      
				)

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    
                    
                      
			}

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    
                    
                      
			# ! 400: Bad Request - attempt to parse as success, otherwise treat as empty/error

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    !
                    
                      
			if (status == 400) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    !
                    
                      
				body <- try(httr2::resp_body_json(resp), silent = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    !
                    
                      
				if (inherits(body, "try-error") || length(body) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    !
                    
                      
					msg <- if (inherits(body, "try-error")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    !
                    
                      
						"Response body could not be parsed as JSON."

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    
                    
                      
					} else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    !
                    
                      
						"Response body was empty."

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    
                    
                      
					}

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    !
                    
                      
					cli::cli_warn(

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    !
                    
                      
						"Query resulted in status 400 (Bad Request) with no parsable data. {msg}"

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    
                    
                      
					)

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    !
                    
                      
					return(tibble::tibble()) # Return empty tibble if no data

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    
                    
                      
				} else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    !
                    
                      
					cli::cli_warn(

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    !
                    
                      
						"Query resulted in status 400 (Bad Request). Body: {jsonlite::toJSON(body, auto_unbox = TRUE)}"

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    
                    
                      
					)

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    !
                    
                      
					return(tibble::tibble())

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    
                    
                      
				}

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      
			}

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    
                    
                      
			# ! 404: Not Found - a common outcome for searches, not a "failure"

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    !
                    
                      
			if (status == 404) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    !
                    
                      
				return(tibble::tibble()) # No results found, return empty tibble

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    
                    
                      
			}

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    
                    
                      
			# ! Other 4xx and 5xx errors

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    !
                    
                      
			if (status >= 400) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    !
                    
                      
				msg <- httr2::resp_status_desc(resp)

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    !
                    
                      
				cli::cli_warn("Query failed with status {status}: {msg}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    !
                    
                      
				return(tibble::tibble(

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    !
                    
                      
					error = msg,

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    !
                    
                      
					message = paste("HTTP status", status)

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    
                    
                      
				))

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    
                    
                      
			}

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    
                    
                      
		}) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    !
                    
                      
			purrr::list_rbind(names_to = "query")

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    
                    
                      
	}

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    
                    
                      
	# POST response parsing ----

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    !
                    
                      
	if (request_method == "POST") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    
                    
                      
		# Process responses chunk by chunk, creating a list of tibbles

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    !
                    
                      
		results <- map2(resps, query_chunks, function(resp, chunk) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    !
                    
                      
			body <- httr2::resp_body_json(resp)

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    !
                    
                      
			body %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    173
                    !
                    
                      
				set_names(chunk) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    174
                    !
                    
                      
				map(., compact) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    !
                    
                      
				map(., ~ purrr::discard(.x, names(.) %in% c('pcCode', 'dtxsid'))) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    176
                    !
                    
                      
				map(., ~ map(., list_c)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    177
                    !
                    
                      
				map(., ~ map(., as_tibble)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    178
                    !
                    
                      
				map(., ~ list_rbind(.x, names_to = 'quality')) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    179
                    !
                    
                      
				list_rbind(., names_to = 'query')

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    !
                    
                      
		}) %>% list_rbind()

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    !
                    
                      
		return(results)

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    
                    
                      
	}

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    
                    
                      
}
