#' @title Download Chemical Image by DTXSID

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#' @description Downloads a chemical image from the EPA's CompTox Chemicals Dashboard API based on the provided DTXSID and saves it to a specified directory.

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' @param query A character vector of DTXSIDs to search for.

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' @param download_dir Optional directory to save the downloaded images. If not specified, a temporary directory will be used.

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A list of file paths to the downloaded images, or an empty list if no images are found.

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom httr2 request

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom httr2 req_headers

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom httr2 req_perform

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom httr2 resp_body_json

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom httr2 resp_body_raw

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom httr2 resp_header

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom purrr map

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom purrr safely

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom cli cli_rule

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom cli cli_dl

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom cli cli_end

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom cli cli_alert_success

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom cli cli_alert_warning

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom fs path_join

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom fs file_exists

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom fs dir_create

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#' \dontrun{

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#' # Download the image for a single DTXSID to a temporary directory

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#' image_files <- get_ct_image(query = "DTXSID7020182")

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#' # Download images for multiple DTXSIDs to a specified directory

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#' image_files <- get_ct_image(query = c("DTXSID7020182", "DTXSID5020452"), download_dir = "~/Downloads/ct_images")

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
get_ct_image <- function(query, download_dir = tempdir()) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
  # Input validation

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    !
                    
                      
  if (!is.character(query)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    !
                    
                      
    stop("query must be a character vector of DTXSIDs.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    !
                    
                      
  if (!is.character(download_dir) || length(download_dir) != 1) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    !
                    
                      
    stop(

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    !
                    
                      
      "download_dir must be a single character string specifying the directory to save images."

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
  # Create the download directory if it doesn't exist

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    !
                    
                      
  if (!fs::dir_exists(download_dir)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    !
                    
                      
    fs::dir_create(download_dir, recurse = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_alert_info("Created download directory: {download_dir}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
  # Prepare the base URL

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    !
                    
                      
  base_url <- "https://api-ccte.epa.gov/chemical/file/image/search/by-dtxsid/"

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      
  # Create debugging messages for the user

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    !
                    
                      
  cli::cli_rule(left = "API payload options")

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    !
                    
                      
  cli::cli_dl(c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
    "Number of compounds" = "{length(query)}",

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    !
                    
                      
    "Download directory" = "{download_dir}"

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      
  ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    !
                    
                      
  cli::cli_rule()

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    !
                    
                      
  cli::cli_end()

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      
  # Function to safely fetch and download image

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    !
                    
                      
  safe_download <- purrr::safely(function(dtxsid) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    !
                    
                      
    req <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    !
                    
                      
      httr2::request(paste0(base_url, dtxsid)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    !
                    
                      
      httr2::req_headers(accept = "application/hal+json")

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    !
                    
                      
    resp <- httr2::req_perform(req)

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    !
                    
                      
    if (httr2::resp_status(resp) == 200) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    !
                    
                      
      content_type <- httr2::resp_header(resp, "content-type")

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    !
                    
                      
      if (grepl("application/hal\\+json", content_type)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    !
                    
                      
        body <- httr2::resp_body_json(resp)

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    !
                    
                      
        if (length(body$`_links`$image$href) > 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    !
                    
                      
          image_url <- body$`_links`$image$href

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    
                    
                      
          # Determine the file extension (e.g., .png, .jpg)

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    !
                    
                      
          file_ext <- tools::file_ext(image_url)

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    !
                    
                      
          if (file_ext == "") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    !
                    
                      
            file_ext <- "png" # Default to png if no extension is found

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    
                    
                      
          }

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
          # Create a filename based on the DTXSID and file extension

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    !
                    
                      
          destfile <- fs::path_join(c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    !
                    
                      
            download_dir,

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    !
                    
                      
            paste0(dtxsid, ".", file_ext)

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      
          ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    
                    
                      
          # Download the image

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    !
                    
                      
          image_req <- httr2::request(image_url)

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    !
                    
                      
          image_resp <- httr2::req_perform(image_req)

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    !
                    
                      
          image_raw <- httr2::resp_body_raw(image_resp)

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    !
                    
                      
          writeBin(image_raw, destfile)

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    !
                    
                      
          cli::cli_alert_success(

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    !
                    
                      
            "Successfully downloaded image for {dtxsid} to {destfile}"

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      
          )

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    !
                    
                      
          return(destfile)

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    
                    
                      
        } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    !
                    
                      
          cli::cli_alert_warning("No image URL found for {dtxsid}")

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    !
                    
                      
          return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    !
                    
                      
      } else if (grepl("image/", content_type)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    
                    
                      
        # The response is directly the image

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    !
                    
                      
        file_ext <- tools::file_ext(httr2::resp_url(resp))

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    !
                    
                      
        if (file_ext == "") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    !
                    
                      
          file_ext <- switch(

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    !
                    
                      
            content_type,

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    !
                    
                      
            "image/png" = "png",

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    !
                    
                      
            "image/jpeg" = "jpg",

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    !
                    
                      
            "image/gif" = "gif",

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    !
                    
                      
            "png"

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    !
                    
                      
          ) # Default to png

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    !
                    
                      
        destfile <- fs::path_join(c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    !
                    
                      
          download_dir,

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    !
                    
                      
          paste0(dtxsid, ".", file_ext)

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    
                    
                      
        ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    !
                    
                      
        image_raw <- httr2::resp_body_raw(resp)

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    !
                    
                      
        writeBin(image_raw, destfile)

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    !
                    
                      
        cli::cli_alert_success(

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    !
                    
                      
          "Successfully downloaded image for {dtxsid} to {destfile}"

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    
                    
                      
        )

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    !
                    
                      
        return(destfile)

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    
                    
                      
      } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    !
                    
                      
        cli::cli_alert_warning(

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    !
                    
                      
          "Unexpected content type {content_type} for {dtxsid}"

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    
                    
                      
        )

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    !
                    
                      
        return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    
                    
                      
    } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    !
                    
                      
      cli::cli_alert_warning(

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    !
                    
                      
        "Request failed for {dtxsid} with status {httr2::resp_status(resp)}"

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    !
                    
                      
      return(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    
                    
                      
  })

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    
                    
                      
  # Download images for all DTXSIDs

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    !
                    
                      
  results <- purrr::map(query, safe_download)

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    
                    
                      
  # Extract the results and errors

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    !
                    
                      
  image_files <- purrr::map(results, "result")

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    !
                    
                      
  errors <- purrr::map(results, "error")

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    
                    
                      
  # Handle errors

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    !
                    
                      
  has_errors <- any(!sapply(errors, is.null))

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    !
                    
                      
  if (has_errors) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_alert_warning("Some requests failed. See errors list for details.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    !
                    
                      
    print(errors) # or handle them in a more user-friendly way

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      
  # Clean up the results (remove NULLs)

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    !
                    
                      
  image_files <- image_files[!sapply(image_files, is.null)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    !
                    
                      
  return(image_files)

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Returns all compounds on a given list

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' Can be used to return all compounds from a single list (e.g.:'PRODWATER') or a list of aggregated lists.

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @param list_name Search parameter (list name or vector of list names)

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @param extract_dtxsids Boolean to pluck out just the DTXSIDs.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @return Returns a character vector (if extract_dtxsids=TRUE) or list of results (if FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' \dontrun{

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'  ct_list(list_name = c("PRODWATER", "CWA311HS"), extract_dtxsids = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
ct_list <- function(list_name, extract_dtxsids = TRUE) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
  # Uppercase list names (API expects uppercase)

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    !
                    
                      
  list_name_upper <- stringr::str_to_upper(list_name)

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
  # Use generic_request with tidy=FALSE to get list output

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    !
                    
                      
  dat <- generic_request(

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    !
                    
                      
    query = list_name_upper,

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    !
                    
                      
    endpoint = "chemical/list/search/by-name/",

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    !
                    
                      
    method = "GET",

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    !
                    
                      
    batch_limit = 1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    !
                    
                      
    tidy = FALSE,

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    !
                    
                      
    projection = 'chemicallistwithdtxsids'

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    !
                    
                      
  if (extract_dtxsids) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
    # Check if dat has duplicate names (multiple results concatenated)

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    !
                    
                      
    if (anyDuplicated(names(dat)) > 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
      # Multiple results - extract all dtxsids fields

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    !
                    
                      
      dtxsid_indices <- which(names(dat) == "dtxsids")

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    !
                    
                      
      dat <- dat[dtxsid_indices] %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    !
                    
                      
        purrr::map(~ stringr::str_split(.x, pattern = ',')) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    !
                    
                      
        unlist() %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    !
                    
                      
        unique()

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
    } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
      # Single result - extract and split directly

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    !
                    
                      
      dat <- dat$dtxsids %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
        stringr::str_split(pattern = ',') %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    !
                    
                      
        unlist() %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    !
                    
                      
        unique()

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    !
                    
                      
  return(dat)

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Grabs all public lists

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' This function has no parameters to search by.

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @param return_dtxsid Boolean; Return all DTXSIDs contained within each list

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @param coerce Boolean; Coerce each list of DTXSIDs into a vector rather than the native string.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @return Returns a tibble of results (or nested list if coerce=TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
ct_lists_all <- function(

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
  return_dtxsid = FALSE,

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
  coerce = FALSE

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
  #cli::cli_alert_info('Grabbing all public lists...')

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
  # Determine projection

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    !
                    
                      
  projection <- if (!return_dtxsid) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    !
                    
                      
    "chemicallistall"

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    !
                    
                      
    "chemicallistwithdtxsids"

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
  # Use generic_request with batch_limit=0 for static endpoint

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    !
                    
                      
  df <- generic_request(

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    !
                    
                      
    query = NULL,  # No query needed for static endpoint

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    !
                    
                      
    endpoint = "chemical/list/all",

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    !
                    
                      
    method = "GET",

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    !
                    
                      
    batch_limit = 0,  # Static endpoint flag

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    !
                    
                      
    tidy = TRUE,

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    !
                    
                      
    projection = projection

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    !
                    
                      
  cli::cli_alert_success('{nrow(df)} lists found!')

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    !
                    
                      
  if (return_dtxsid & coerce) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_alert_warning('Coercing DTXSID strings per list to list-column!')

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    !
                    
                      
    df <- df %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    !
                    
                      
      split(.$listName) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
      purrr::map(., as.list) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    !
                    
                      
      purrr::map(

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
        .,

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
        ~ {

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    !

        cat(typeof(query))

    } else {

#' Create a similarity list from chemical cluster data

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    
                    
                      
#' @description Converts a similarity matrix into a long-format data frame.

#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    
                    
                      
#' @param chemi_cluster_data A list object containing chemical cluster data, including `mol_names` and a `similarity` matrix.

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    
                    
                      
#' @returns A tibble with columns for parent and child chemical identifiers, their names, and the similarity value between them. The function will error if `chemi_cluster_data` is `NULL` or missing.

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    
                    
                      
chemi_cluster_sim_list <- function(chemi_cluster_data) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    !
                    
                      
	if (missing(chemi_cluster_data) || is.null(chemi_cluster_data)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    !
                    
                      
		cli::cli_abort("Missing chemi_cluster_data!")

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    
                    
                      
	}

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    !
                    
                      
	mol_names <- chemi_cluster_data$mol_names

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    !
                    
                      
	similarity <- chemi_cluster_data$similarity

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    !
                    
                      
	sim_list <- similarity %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    !
                    
                      
		set_names(., mol_names$name) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    !
                    
                      
		map(., ~ set_names(.x, mol_names$name)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    !
                    
                      
		map(., ~ enframe(.x, name = 'child', value = 'value')) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    !
                    
                      
		list_rbind(., names_to = 'parent') %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    
                    
                      
	# ! NOTE Removes perfect correlations

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    !
                    
                      
		filter(parent != child) #%>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    
                    
                      
	# ! NOTE Commented out due to DTXSID not always being present.

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    
                    
                      
	# left_join(., mol_names, join_by('parent' == 'name')) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    
                    
                      
	# left_join(., mol_names, join_by('child' == 'name')) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    
                    
                      
	# select(

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    
                    
                      
	# 	parent,

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    
                    
                      
	# 	parent_name = name.x,

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    
                    
                      
	# 	child,

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    
                    
                      
	# 	child_name = name.y,

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    
                    
                      
	# 	value

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    
                    
                      
	# )

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    !
                    
                      
	return(sim_list)

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    
                    
                      
}
