                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Resolve chemical identifiers using an external API

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' This function takes a vector of chemical identifiers as input and uses an external API

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' to resolve them. It sends a POST request to the API endpoint, passing the identifiers

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' in the request body. The API response is then parsed to extract the 'chemical' field

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' from each returned object.

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @param query A character vector of chemical identifiers.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @param id_type A single string; one of `"DTXSID"`, `"DTXCID"`, `"SMILES"`,

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#'   `"MOL"`, `"CAS"`, `"Name"`, `"InChI"`, `"InChIKey"`, `"InChIKey_1"`, or

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'   `"AnyId"`. Optional.

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' @param is_fuzzy A single logical value. Optional.

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @param fuzzy_type A single string; one of `"Not"`, `"Anywhere"`, `"Start"`,

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'   `"Word"`, `"CloseSyntactic"`, or `"CloseSemantic"`. Required when

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'   `is_fuzzy` is `TRUE`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' @param mol A single logical value. If `TRUE`, returns a V3000 mol array.

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#'   Optional.

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A list of resolved chemical information. Returns an empty list if no

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'   results are found. Errors if the API request fails.

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
chemi_resolver <- function(

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
	query,

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
	id_type = NULL,

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
	is_fuzzy = FALSE,

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
	fuzzy_type,

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
	mol = FALSE

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
	# NOTE creates simple list if the length is 1, otherwise allows for boxed list

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    !
                    
                      
	query = as.list(query)

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    !
                    
                      
	init_query <- length(query)

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    !
                    
                      
	mult_count <- ceiling(length(query) / 200)

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    !
                    
                      
	mult_request <- mult_count > 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    !
                    
                      
	if (length(query) > 200) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    !
                    
                      
		query_list <- split(

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    !
                    
                      
			query,

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
			rep(1:mult_count, each = 200, length.out = length(query))

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
		)

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
	} else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    !
                    
                      
		query_list <- list(query)

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
	}

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
	# Check if the id_type argument is provided.

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      
	# If not, stop execution and inform the user.

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    !
                    
                      
	if (missing(id_type) || is.null(id_type)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    !
                    
                      
		cli::cli_alert_danger(

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    !
                    
                      
			'Missing ID type, defaulting to {cli::col_red("AnyID")}'

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    
                    
                      
		)

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
		id_type <- 'AnyId'

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    
                    
                      
	}

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    
                    
                      
	# Validate the provided id_type against a predefined list of allowed values.

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    
                    
                      
	# match.arg will throw an error if the user's input is not one of the choices.

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    !
                    
                      
	id_type <- rlang::arg_match(

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    !
                    
                      
		id_type,

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    !
                    
                      
		values = c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    !
                    
                      
			'DTXSID',

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    !
                    
                      
			'DTXCID',

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    !
                    
                      
			'SMILES',

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    !
                    
                      
			'MOL',

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    !
                    
                      
			'CAS',

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    !
                    
                      
			'Name',

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    !
                    
                      
			'InChI',

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    !
                    
                      
			'InChIKey',

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    !
                    
                      
			'InChIKey_1',

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    !
                    
                      
			'AnyId'

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    
                    
                      
		)

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    
                    
                      
	)

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      
	# If fuzzy search is disabled, set the type to "Not". This ensures a

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    
                    
                      
	# valid default is passed to arg_match, as fuzzy_type lacks a default.

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    !
                    
                      
	if (!is_fuzzy) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    !
                    
                      
		fuzzy_type <- "Not"

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    
                    
                      
		# If fuzzy search is enabled, a `fuzzy_type` becomes mandatory.

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    !
                    
                      
	} else if (missing(fuzzy_type) || is.null(fuzzy_type)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    !
                    
                      
		cli::cli_abort("When `is_fuzzy` is TRUE, a `fuzzy_type` must be provided.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      
	}

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    
                    
                      
	# Validate the provided fuzzy_type against a predefined list of allowed values.

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    
                    
                      
	# match.arg will throw an error if the user's input is not one of the choices.

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    !
                    
                      
	fuzzy_type <- rlang::arg_match(

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    !
                    
                      
		fuzzy_type,

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    !
                    
                      
		values = c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    !
                    
                      
			"Not",

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    !
                    
                      
			"Anywhere",

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    !
                    
                      
			"Start",

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    !
                    
                      
			"Word",

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    !
                    
                      
			"CloseSyntactic",

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    !
                    
                      
			"CloseSemantic"

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    
                    
                      
		)

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    
                    
                      
	)

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    
                    
                      
	# Returns the V3000 mol array

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    
                    
                      
	# Checks for parameter validity

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    !
                    
                      
	if (!is.logical(mol) || missing(mol) || is.null(mol)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    !
                    
                      
		if (as.logical(Sys.getenv('run_verbose'))) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    !
                    
                      
			cli::cli_alert_warning(

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    !
                    
                      
				'Mol parameter requires BOOLEAN value! Defaulting to {cli::col_red("FALSE")}.'

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    
                    
                      
			)

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    
                    
                      
		}

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    !
                    
                      
		mol <- FALSE

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    
                    
                      
	} else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    !
                    
                      
		mol <- as.logical(mol)

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    
                    
                      
	}

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    !
                    
                      
	req_list <- map(

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    !
                    
                      
		query_list,

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    !
                    
                      
		function(query_part) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    !
                    
                      
			request(Sys.getenv('chemi_burl')) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    !
                    
                      
				req_method("POST") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    !
                    
                      
				req_url_path_append("resolver/lookup") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    !
                    
                      
				req_headers(Accept = "application/json, text/plain, */*") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    !
                    
                      
				req_body_json(

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    !
                    
                      
					list(

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    !
                    
                      
						fuzzy = unbox(fuzzy_type),

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    !
                    
                      
						ids = query_part,

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    !
                    
                      
						idsType = unbox(id_type),

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    !
                    
                      
						mol = unbox(mol)

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    
                    
                      
					)

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    
                    
                      
				)

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    
                    
                      
		}

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    
                    
                      
	)

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    !
                    
                      
	if (as.logical(Sys.getenv('run_debug'))) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    !
                    
                      
		return(req_list %>% pluck(., 1) %>% req_dry_run())

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    
                    
                      
	}

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    !
                    
                      
	if (mult_request) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    !
                    
                      
		resp_list <- req_list %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    !
                    
                      
			req_perform_sequential(., on_error = 'continue')

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    
                    
                      
	} else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    !
                    
                      
		resp_list <- list(req_perform(req_list[[1]]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    
                    
                      
	}

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    !
                    
                      
	body_list <- resp_list %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    !
                    
                      
		map(., function(r) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    !
                    
                      
			if (resp_status(r) < 200 || resp_status(r) >= 300) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    !
                    
                      
				cli::cli_abort(paste(

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    !
                    
                      
					"API request failed with status",

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    !
                    
                      
					resp_status(r)

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    
                    
                      
				))

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      
			}

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    !
                    
                      
			body <- resp_body_json(r)

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    !
                    
                      
			if (length(body) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    !
                    
                      
				cli::cli_alert_warning("No results found for the given query.")

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    !
                    
                      
				return(list())

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    
                    
                      
			}

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    !
                    
                      
			return(body)

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    
                    
                      
		}) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    !
                    
                      
		list_c()

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    !
                    
                      
	cli_rule(left = 'Resolver results')

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    !
                    
                      
	cli_dl(

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    !
                    
                      
		c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    !
                    
                      
			'Number of compounds requested' = '{init_query}',

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    !
                    
                      
			'Number of batches' = '{mult_count}',

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    !
                    
                      
			'Number of compounds found' = '{length(body_list)}',

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    !
                    
                      
			'ID Type' = '{id_type}',

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    !
                    
                      
			'Fuzzy Search' = '{is_fuzzy}',

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    !
                    
                      
			'Fuzzy Type' = '{fuzzy_type}',

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    !
                    
                      
			'Mol' = '{mol}'

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    
                    
                      
		)

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    
                    
                      
	)

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    !
                    
                      
	cli::cli_rule()

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    !
                    
                      
	cli::cli_end()

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    173
                    !
                    
                      
	return(

                    		
                  

                  

                    174
                    !
                    
                      
		body_list %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    !
                    
                      
			map(., ~ list_flatten(.x, name_spec = '{inner}') %>% as_tibble()) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    176
                    !
                    
                      
			list_rbind() %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    177
                    
                    
                      
			#select(-chemId) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    178
                    !
                    
                      
			rename_with(

                    		
                  

                  

                    179
                    !
                    
                      
				~ c(query = "raw_query", sid = "dtxsid", cid = "dtxcid")[.x],

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    !
                    
                      
				.cols = any_of(c("query", "sid", "cid"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    
                    
                      
			) %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    !
                    
                      
			dplyr::relocate(any_of("raw_query"), .before = any_of("dtxcid"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    
                    
                      
	)

                    		
                  

                  

                    184
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    185
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' Retrieve a specific safety section for a chemical compound from a remote API.

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' This function queries an API to retrieve a specific safety section for a list

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' of chemical compounds identified by their DTXSID. It validates the section

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' request and provides informative messages about the process.

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @param query A character vector of DTXSIDs for the chemical compounds.

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param section A character string specifying the safety section to retrieve.

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#'   Must be one of: 'GHS Classification', 'Regulatory Information',

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#'   'Record Description', 'Regulatory Information', 'Accidental Release

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#'   Measures', 'Fire Fighting', 'Transport Information', 'NFPA Hazard

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'   Classification', 'Other Safety Information', 'Stability and Reactivity'.

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A list where each element corresponds to a DTXSID in the `query`. Each

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'   element contains the retrieved data for the specified `section` as a list.

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'   If no data is found, the function returns `NULL` and displays an error message.

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' \dontrun{

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' # Assuming the CHEMI_BURL environment variable is set correctly

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#' # and the API is accessible.

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#' # Retrieve the GHS Classification for a single compound.

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#' ghs_data <- chemi_safety_section(query = "DTXSID0000001", section = "GHS Classification")

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#' # Retrieve the Regulatory Information for multiple compounds.

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#' regulatory_data <- chemi_safety_section(

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#'   query = c("DTXSID0000001", "DTXSID0000002"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#'   section = "Regulatory Information"

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#' )

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#' # Handle cases where no data is found.

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
#' no_data <- chemi_safety_section(query = "DTXSID_INVALID", section = "GHS Classification")

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
#' if (is.null(no_data)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
#'   cat("No data found for the specified query.\n")

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
chemi_safety_section <- function(query, section = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
  # Check if the section is missing. If so, abort with an error message.

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    !
                    
                      
  if (is.null(section) | missing(section)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_abort('Missing section!')

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
  # Check if the requested section is valid. If not, abort with an error message.

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
  if (

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    !
                    
                      
    !section %in%

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    !
                    
                      
      c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    !
                    
                      
        'GHS Classification',

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    !
                    
                      
        'Regulatory Information',

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    !
                    
                      
        'Record Description',

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    !
                    
                      
        'Regulatory Information',

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    !
                    
                      
        'Accidental Release Measures',

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
        'Fire Fighting',

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    !
                    
                      
        'Transport Information',

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    !
                    
                      
        'NFPA Hazard Classification',

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    !
                    
                      
        'Other Safety Information',

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    !
                    
                      
        'Stability and Reactivity'

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      
  ) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_abort('Improper section request!')

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      
  # Check if the query is missing. If so, abort with an error message.

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    !
                    
                      
  if (is.null(query) | missing(query)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    !
                    
                      
    cli::cli_abort('Request missing')

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
  # Initialize a list to store the results for each chemical compound.

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    !
                    
                      
  chemicals <- vector(mode = "list", length = length(query))

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    
                    
                      
  # Display information about the safety section payload options.

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    !
                    
                      
  cli_rule(left = "Safety section payload options")

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    !
                    
                      
  cli_dl(

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    !
                    
                      
    c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    !
                    
                      
      "Number of compounds" = "{length(query)}",

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    !
                    
                      
      "Section" = "{section}"

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    !
                    
                      
  cli_rule()

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    !
                    
                      
  cli_end()

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    
                    
                      
  # Create a list of API requests for each DTXSID in the query.

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    !
                    
                      
  req_list <- map(

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    !
                    
                      
    query,

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    
                    
                      
    ~ {

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    !
                    
                      
      request(

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    !
                    
                      
        base_url = Sys.getenv('chemi_burl') # Get the base URL from the environment variable.

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    
                    
                      
      ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    !
                    
                      
        req_url_path_append("resolver/pubchem-section") %>% # Append the API endpoint.

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    !
                    
                      
        req_url_query(query = .x) %>% # Add the DTXSID as a query parameter.

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    !
                    
                      
        req_url_query(idType = 'DTXSID') %>% # Specify the ID type as DTXSID.

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    !
                    
                      
        req_url_query(section = section) # Add the requested section as a query parameter.

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    
                    
                      
  # Perform the API requests sequentially, continuing on error, and displaying a progress bar.

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    !
                    
                      
  resps <- req_list %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    !
                    
                      
    req_perform_sequential(., on_error = 'continue', progress = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    
                    
                      
  # Process the API responses.

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    !
                    
                      
  df <- resps %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    !
                    
                      
    set_names(query) %>% # Set the names of the responses to the DTXSIDs.

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    !
                    
                      
    resps_successes() %>% # Filter out unsuccessful responses.

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    !
                    
                      
    resps_data(\(resp) resp_body_json(resp)) %>% # Extract the JSON data from the successful responses.

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    !
                    
                      
    map(

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    
                    
                      
      .,

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    !
                    
                      
      ~ pluck(., 'swr') %>% # Extract the 'swr' element from each response.

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    !
                    
                      
        list_flatten() %>% # Flatten the list.

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    !
                    
                      
        pluck(., 'section', 'Section') # Extract the 'Section' element.

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    
                    
                      
    ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    !
                    
                      
    map(

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    
                    
                      
      .,

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    
                    
                      
      ~ {

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    
                    
                      
        # Iterate through each element in the list.

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    
                    
                      
        # sublists names

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    
                    
                      
        # Extract "TOCHeading" from each sublist within the current element.

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    !
                    
                      
        df <- map(

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    
                    
                      
          .,

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    
                    
                      
          ~ {

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    !
                    
                      
            headers <- pluck(.x, "TOCHeading")

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    
                    
                      
          }

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    
                    
                      
        ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    
                    
                      
          # Combine the extracted headers into a single vector.

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    !
                    
                      
          list_c()

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    
                    
                      
        # Assign the extracted headers as names to the sublists in the current element.

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    !
                    
                      
        setNames(.x, df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    
                    
                      
    ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    !
                    
                      
    map(

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    
                    
                      
      .,

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    
                    
                      
      ~ {

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    !
                    
                      
        map(., ~ pluck(.x, 'Information')) %>% # Extract the 'Information' element.

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    !
                    
                      
          map(

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    
                    
                      
            .,

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    
                    
                      
            ~ {

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
