#' Checks if a string is a syntactically and algorithmically valid CASRN

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' A valid CAS Registry Number (CASRN) is a string in the format "dd...d-dd-d",

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' containing 5 to 10 digits in total. The final digit is a check-digit

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' calculated using a specific algorithm. This function validates both the

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' format and the check-digit calculation.

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @param x A character vector of potential CASRN strings.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A logical vector of the same length as `x`. Returns `TRUE` for

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'   each valid CASRN, `FALSE` for invalid ones, and `NA` for `NA` inputs.

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom stringr str_detect str_remove_all str_split_i

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' is_cas("50-00-0")  # Valid

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' is_cas("50-00-1")  # Invalid check digit

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' is_cas("7732-18-5") # Valid

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#' is_cas("100-42-5")  # Valid

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' is_cas("not-a-casrn")

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#' is_cas(c("50-00-0", "50-00-1", NA, "7732-18-5"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
is_cas <- function(x) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
  # The check-digit algorithm needs to be applied to each element.

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
  # vapply is a safe and efficient way to do this.

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    !
                    
                      
  vapply(x, FUN = function(cas_str) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
    # Immediately return NA for NA inputs

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    !
                    
                      
    if (is.na(cas_str)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    !
                    
                      
      return(NA)

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
    # 1. Check the basic format: xx-yy-z with 2-7 digits in the first part.

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
    # This is a fast way to reject clearly invalid strings.

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    !
                    
                      
    format_regex <- "^\\d{2,7}-\\d{2}-\\d$"

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    !
                    
                      
    if (!stringr::str_detect(cas_str, format_regex)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    !
                    
                      
      return(FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
    # 2. Perform the check-digit calculation.

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
    # Get the provided check-digit (the last character).

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
    expected_check_digit <- as.integer(stringr::str_split_i(cas_str, "-", 3))

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
    # Get the number part (everything before the last digit and hyphen).

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    !
                    
                      
    number_part <- stringr::str_remove_all(cas_str, "-\\d$")

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    !
                    
                      
    number_part <- stringr::str_remove_all(number_part, "-")

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
    # Split into individual digits, reverse, and calculate.

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    !
                    
                      
    digits <- as.integer(strsplit(number_part, "")[[1]])

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    !
                    
                      
    reversed_digits <- rev(digits)

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    
                    
                      
    # The check-digit is the sum of (digit * position) modulo 10

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    !
                    
                      
    calculated_check_digit <- sum(reversed_digits * seq_along(reversed_digits)) %% 10

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    
                    
                      
    # Return TRUE only if the calculation matches the provided check-digit.

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    !
                    
                      
    return(calculated_check_digit == expected_check_digit)

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    !
                    
                      
  }, FUN.VALUE = logical(1), USE.NAMES = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    
                    
                      
#' Coerces and validates a string to a standard CASRN format

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      
#' This function attempts to convert a string into a valid Chemical Abstracts

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      
#' Service Registry Number (CASRN). It handles common data quality issues such

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    
                    
                      
#' as extra non-digit characters, missing hyphens, and leading zeros.

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    
                    
                      
#' The function extracts all digits, trims any leading zeros, formats the

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    
                    
                      
#' result into the standard "xx-yy-z" structure, and then validates it using

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    
                    
                      
#' the `is_cas()` check-digit algorithm.

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      
#' @param x A character vector of potential CASRN strings.

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A character vector of the same length as `x`. Returns the correctly

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    
                    
                      
#'   formatted, canonical CASRN string if valid, otherwise returns `NA_character_`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom stringr str_remove_all str_sub

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
#' @seealso [is_cas()] for the underlying validation logic.

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      
#' # Handles standard and padded formats

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      
#' as_cas("50-00-0")

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    
                    
                      
#' as_cas("0050-00-0") # Padded with leading zeros

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    
                    
                      
#' as_cas("000575-38-2") # Another padded example

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    
                    
                      
#' # Handles extra characters and missing hyphens

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    
                    
                      
#' as_cas("CAS: 7732-18-5")

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    
                    
                      
#' as_cas("50000")

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      
#' # Returns NA for invalid CASRNs

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    
                    
                      
#' as_cas("50-00-1") # Invalid check digit

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    
                    
                      
#' as_cas("not-a-casrn")

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    
                    
                      
as_cas <- function(x) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    !
                    
                      
  vapply(x, FUN = function(cas_str) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    !
                    
                      
    if (is.na(cas_str)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    96
                    !
                    
                      
      return(NA_character_)

                    		
                  

                  

                    97
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    98
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    99
                    
                    
                      
    # 1. Extract only the digits from the string.

                    		
                  

                  

                    100
                    !
                    
                      
    digits_only <- stringr::str_remove_all(cas_str, "[^0-9]")

                    		
                  

                  

                    101
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    102
                    
                    
                      
    # If no digits were found, it's invalid.

                    		
                  

                  

                    103
                    !
                    
                      
    if (nchar(digits_only) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    104
                    !
                    
                      
      return(NA_character_)

                    		
                  

                  

                    105
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    
                    
                      
    # --- NEW STEP: Trim leading zeros ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    
                    
                      
    # The as.numeric -> as.character trick is a robust way to do this.

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    
                    
                      
    # It correctly handles "0050" -> "50" and "0" -> "0".

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    !
                    
                      
    digits_only <- as.character(as.numeric(digits_only))

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    
                    
                      
    # 2. A CASRN must have between 5 and 10 digits *after trimming*.

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    !
                    
                      
    n <- nchar(digits_only)

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    !
                    
                      
    if (n < 5 || n > 10) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    !
                    
                      
      return(NA_character_)

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    
                    
                      
    # 3. Reconstruct the string in the standard format.

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    !
                    
                      
    first_part <- stringr::str_sub(digits_only, 1, n - 3)

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    !
                    
                      
    middle_part <- stringr::str_sub(digits_only, n - 2, n - 1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    !
                    
                      
    check_digit <- stringr::str_sub(digits_only, n, n)

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    !
                    
                      
    formatted_cas <- paste(first_part, middle_part, check_digit, sep = "-")

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    
                    
                      
    # 4. Use our strict validator function to check the result.

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    !
                    
                      
    if (isTRUE(is_cas(formatted_cas))) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    !
                    
                      
      return(formatted_cas)

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    
                    
                      
    } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    !
                    
                      
      return(NA_character_)

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    !
                    
                      
  }, FUN.VALUE = character(1), USE.NAMES = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    
                    
                      
}

                    135
                    
                    
                      
#' Extracts all valid CASRNs from a character vector

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    
                    
                      
#' This function searches for and extracts all valid Chemical Abstracts Service

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    
                    
                      
#' Registry Numbers (CASRNs) from a character vector. It uses a flexible

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    
                    
                      
#' pattern to find candidate strings (including those without hyphens) and then

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    
                    
                      
#' validates each one using the `as_cas()` coercion and validation function.

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    
                    
                      
#' @param x A character vector of text to be searched.

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A list of character vectors. Each element of the list corresponds

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    
                    
                      
#'   to an element of the input `x` and contains all valid CASRNs found.

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      
#'   An empty `character(0)` vector indicates no valid CASRNs were found for

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    
                    
                      
#'   that input string.

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom stringr str_extract_all

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    
                    
                      
#' @seealso [as_cas()] and [is_cas()] for the underlying coercion and

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    
                    
                      
#'   validation logic.

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    
                    
                      
#' text <- c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    
                    
                      
#'   "The CAS for formaldehyde is 50-00-0, and water is 7732-18-5.",

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    
                    
                      
#'   "An invalid number is 50-00-1, but a padded one is 007732-18-5.",

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    
                    
                      
#'   "No hyphens: 50000.",

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    
                    
                      
#'   "No valid CASRNs in this string.",

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    
                    
                      
#'   NA

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    
                    
                      
#' )

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    
                    
                      
#' extract_cas(text)

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    
                    
                      
#' # [[1]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    
                    
                      
#' # [1] "50-00-0"   "7732-18-5"

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    
                    
                      
#' #

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    
                    
                      
#' # [[2]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    
                    
                      
#' # [1] "7732-18-5"

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    
                    
                      
#' #

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    
                    
                      
#' # [[3]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    
                    
                      
#' # [1] "50-00-0"

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    
                    
                      
#' #

                    		
                  

                  

                    173
                    
                    
                      
#' # [[4]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    174
                    
                    
                      
#' # character(0)

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    
                    
                      
#' #

                    		
                  

                  

                    176
                    
                    
                      
#' # [[5]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    177
                    
                    
                      
#' # character(0)

                    		
                  

                  

                    178
                    
                    
                      
extract_cas <- function(x) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    179
                    
                    
                      
  # --- Pass 1: Find Potential Candidates ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    
                    
                      
  # This regex is intentionally flexible. It looks for "words" that consist

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    
                    
                      
  # of 5 to 12 digits and hyphens. This will capture well-formatted CASRNs,

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    
                    
                      
  # those with missing hyphens, and padded ones.

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    !
                    
                      
  candidate_regex <- "\\b[0-9-]{5,12}\\b"

                    		
                  

                  

                    184
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    185
                    
                    
                      
  # Extract all candidates into a list of character vectors.

                    		
                  

                  

                    186
                    !
                    
                      
  candidates_list <- stringr::str_extract_all(x, candidate_regex)

                    		
                  

                  

                    187
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    188
                    
                    
                      
  # --- Pass 2: Validate Each Candidate ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    189
                    
                    
                      
  # Use lapply to iterate over the list. For each vector of candidates,

                    		
                  

                  

                    190
                    
                    
                      
  # apply as_cas() and keep only the valid results.

                    		
                  

                  

                    191
                    !
                    
                      
  lapply(candidates_list, function(candidates) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    192
                    !
                    
                      
    if (length(candidates) == 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    193
                    !
                    
                      
      return(character(0))

                    		
                  

                  

                    194
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    195
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    196
                    
                    
                      
    # as_cas() will clean, format, and validate each candidate.

                    		
                  

                  

                    197
                    
                    
                      
    # It returns a valid CASRN string or NA.

                    		
                  

                  

                    198
                    !
                    
                      
    validated_results <- as_cas(candidates)

                    		
                  

                  

                    199
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    200
                    
                    
                      
    # Remove the NAs to keep only the successfully validated CASRNs.

                    		
                  

                  

                    201
                    !
                    
                      
    validated_results[!is.na(validated_results)]

                    		
                  

                  

                    202
                    
                    
                      
  })

                    		
                  

                  

                    203
                    
                    
                      
}

#' Detects chemical mixtures by name based on ratio patterns

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' This function searches a vector of chemical names for patterns indicating a

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' ratio, such as "(1:1)" or "(2:1)". It is useful for identifying potential

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' mixtures that might not be flagged by other means. The search is robust to

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' extra whitespace.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param name_vector A character vector of chemical names to search.

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A logical vector of the same length as `name_vector`. Returns `TRUE`

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#'   if a ratio pattern is found, `FALSE` if not, and `NA` for `NA` inputs.

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom stringr str_detect

                    		
                  

                  

                    15

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' test_names <- c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#'   "Ethanol, water (1:1)",

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#'   "Sodium chloride",

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#'   "Styrene-butadiene copolymer (3:1)",

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'   "A name with extra spaces ( 2 : 1 )",

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#'   "A name with decimals (1.5:1)",

                    		
                  

                  

                    23

                    24

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#'   NA

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#' )

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#' extract_mixture(names)

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#' test_names %>% enframe(., name = 'idx', value = 'name') %>% mutate(bool_mix = extract_mixture(name))

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#' # Expected output: TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, FALSE, NA

extract_mixture <- function(name_vector) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    !
                    
                      
  stopifnot(is.character(name_vector))

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
  # Core ratio like "2:1", "1.5/1", "3-2"

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    !
                    
                      
  ratio_core <- "\\d+(?:\\.\\d+)?\\s*[:/\\-]\\s*\\d+(?:\\.\\d+)?"

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
  # Optional units after ratio

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    !
                    
                      
  units_opt <- "(?:\\s*(?:w/w|v/v|wt%|vol%))?"

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
  # Allow ratios with or without surrounding () or []

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    !
                    
                      
  pattern <- paste0("(?:\\(|\\[)?\\s*", ratio_core, units_opt, "\\s*(?:\\)|\\])?")

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    !
                    
                      
  stringr::str_detect(name_vector, pattern)

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
}

# In file: R/extract_formulas.R (or wherever the factory is)

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' Creates a highly robust, two-pass function for extracting molecular formulas

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' This internal "factory" function builds a pre-validated, high-performance

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' extractor that finds and validates chemical formulas only when they appear

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' inside parentheses or square brackets. It is designed to run once when the

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' package is loaded and return a closure that performs fast extraction.

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' Performance notes:

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' - The list of element symbols and the validator regex are built once, avoiding

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'   repeated string assembly and allocations on every call.

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' - stringr/stringi still compile the regex internally at match-time, but

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#'   pre-building the long alternations and groups avoids per-call construction

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'   overhead and improves maintainability.

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' Robustness notes (updated):

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' - Correct handling of bracket characters (explicit alternation instead of a

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#'   fragile character class).

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' - Candidate finder allows spaces, middle dot (), plus/minus, and periods inside

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'   bracketed content so complexes and hydrates are captured.

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' - Roman numeral filter is case-insensitive and whitespace-tolerant to avoid

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#'   misclassifying oxidation states like "(III)" or "( ii )" as formulas.

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#' - Carbon backbone range filter recognizes hyphen and en dash (e.g., "C912").

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A function for extracting molecular formulas from within enclosures.

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#' @noRd

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
create_formula_extractor_final <- function() {

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
  # --- ONE-TIME EXPENSIVE SETUP ---

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
  # Periodic table symbols (including lanthanides/actinides + common elements)

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
	#fmt:skip

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    !
                    
                      
  elements_list <- c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    !
                    
                      
    'He','Li','Be','Ne','Na','Mg','Al','Si','Cl','Ar','Ca','Sc','Ti','Cr','Mn','Fe','Co','Ni','Cu','Zn','Ga','Ge','As','Se',

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    !
                    
                      
    'Br','Kr','Rb','Sr','Zr','Nb','Mo','Tc','Ru','Rh','Pd','Ag','Cd','In','Sn','Sb','Te','Xe','Cs','Ba','La','Ce','Pr','Nd',

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    !
                    
                      
    'Pm','Sm','Eu','Gd','Tb','Dy','Ho','Er','Tm','Yb','Lu','Hf','Ta','Re','Os','Ir','Pt','Au','Hg','Tl','Pb','Bi','Po','At',

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    !
                    
                      
    'Rn','Fr','Ra','Ac','Th','Pa','Np','Pu','Am','Cm','Bk','Cf','Es','Fm','Md','No','Lr','Rf','Db','Sg','Bh','Hs','Mt','Ds',

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    !
                    
                      
    'Rg','Cn','Nh','Fl','Mc','Lv','Ts','Og','H','B','C','N','O','F','P','S','K','V','I','Y','W','U'

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    !
                    
                      
  elements_pattern <- paste(elements_list, collapse = "|")

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    !
                    
                      
  element_chunk   <- glue::glue("(?:{elements_pattern})\\d*")

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    !
                    
                      
  group_chunk     <- glue::glue("(?:\\((?:{element_chunk})+\\)\\d*|\\[(?:{element_chunk})+\\]\\d*)")

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    !
                    
                      
  validator_regex <- glue::glue("^(?:{element_chunk}|{group_chunk})+(?:[+-]\\d*)?$")

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
  # FIX: Do NOT allow '(' or ')' inside the (...) alternative; allow them inside [...] only.

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    !
                    
                      
  candidate_regex <- "(\\([A-Za-z0-9+\\-\\.\\s]*\\)|\\[[A-Za-z0-9()+\\-\\.\\s]*\\])"

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    !
                    
                      
  roman_numeral_regex <- "(?i)^\\s*(?:i|v|x|l|c|d|m)+\\s*$"

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    !
                    
                      
  carbon_range_regex  <- "^\\s*C\\d+\\s*[-]\\s*\\d+\\s*$"

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    !
                    
                      
  function(text_vector) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    !
                    
                      
    candidates <- stringr::str_extract_all(text_vector, candidate_regex)

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    !
                    
                      
    lapply(candidates, function(cand_list) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    !
                    
                      
      if (length(cand_list) == 0) return(character(0))

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    !
                    
                      
      trimmed <- stringr::str_sub(cand_list, 2, -2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    !
                    
                      
      trimmed <- stringr::str_squish(trimmed)

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    !
                    
                      
      keep_roman  <- !stringr::str_detect(trimmed, roman_numeral_regex)

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    !
                    
                      
      keep_carbon <- !stringr::str_detect(trimmed, carbon_range_regex)

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    !
                    
                      
      cleaned     <- stringr::str_replace_all(trimmed, "[\\.\\s]+", "")

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    !
                    
                      
      is_formula  <- stringr::str_detect(cleaned, validator_regex)

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    !
                    
                      
      res <- trimmed[keep_roman & keep_carbon & is_formula]

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    !
                    
                      
      unique(res)  # de-duplicate while preserving order

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    
                    
                      
#' Extract molecular formulas from text

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    
                    
                      
#' Finds and returns chemically valid molecular formulas from a character vector,

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      
#' restricted to content inside parentheses or square brackets.

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    
                    
                      
#' Behavior:

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    
                    
                      
#' - Correctly handles parentheses, square brackets, stoichiometric numbers, and

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    
                    
                      
#'   grouped substructures (e.g., "(NH3)2").

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    
                    
                      
#' - Recognizes complexes and hydrates inside brackets when they include spaces,

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      
#'   middle dot (), plus/minus, or periods (these are normalized before validation).

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    
                    
                      
#' - Ignores oxidation state Roman numerals in brackets, e.g., "(III)" or "( ii )".

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    
                    
                      
#' - Excludes carbon backbone ranges like "C912".

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    
                    
                      
#' @param text_vector A character vector of text to search.

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    
                    
                      
#' @return A list of character vectors. Each element corresponds to one input

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    
                    
                      
#'   string and contains all formulas found inside its bracketed content.

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom stringr str_extract_all str_detect str_squish str_replace_all

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    
                    
                      
#' @importFrom glue glue

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    
                    
                      
#' texts <- c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    
                    
                      
#'   "Water (H2O) and ethanol (C2H5OH).",

                    		
                  

                  

                    95

                    27
                    !
                    
                      
      dplyr::select(

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    !
                    
                      
        dtxsid = dplyr::any_of(c("query", "value", "sid")),

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    !

                    30

                    31
